name: Sunken Gardens
address: S 27th St & Capitol Pkwy, Lincoln, NE 68502, USA
reviews:
Beautiful evening with my girlfriend for her birthday. Even with the recent frost killing off lots of plant life if you haven't seen it it's still a very unique escape from the urban jungle of city life. I'll post another review this summer with pictures when they start fresh plants.

Definitely worth seeing.

We stopped here on the way to Colorado. It was beautiful! Loved the variety of plants. It being free was a huge bonus too. If it wasn't raining we probably could have spent a few hours at the gardens.

Free admission. Always beautiful in the summer. So many different varieties of butterflies and dragonflies. We love going and looking at all the variety of flowers. Great place for family pictures, weddings, senior photos. If you go on the weekend, don't be surprised if you run into a wedding party. Definitely my favorite garden in Lincoln.
Take a nice stroll around the garden and enjoy yourself, then head over to the rose garden across the street. Very pretty and the variety of roses is amazing.

What an amazing public park! This is an expansive public space with lush gardens, statuary and water features. I can’t believe it’s free to get in. Parking is very limited so you may have to do off street parking. Continue across the street to stroll through the rose garden and see the fountain. The day I was there a vendor was open selling drinks and snacks.

name: Pioneers Park Nature Center
address: 3201 S Coddington Ave, Lincoln, NE 68522, USA
reviews: Really well maintained trails. Great for families. Paved and gravel trails. Nature center. Going to see the bison is so cool. There has been times where people's cars have been broken into, so lock your cars and don't bring valuables. I've never run into this problem, but it has happened to people I know. This is one of my favorite parks in Lincoln

Beautiful park! It had roads for easy driving access and paved paths we could walk on. We came to see the pillars that have some cool history. It has a plaque telling you about them and how they were originally in DC.

Pioneers park is lovely this time of year (snow) well all the time really.  It's good for hiking, biking and wildlife watching. There is a nice play ground right by the picnic area, oh and the picnic area has grills and is large enough to accommodate large groups of folks without being bunched together like sardines.  This has been a favorite backdrop for photo shoots of all kinds... engagement, wedding and senior high portraits.

It's not that far from my residence but I don't get to go there nearly enough in the colder than I can handle weather. This is my favorite park in Lincoln and as long as I've lived here I am ashamed to admit that I have not seen half of the place. I hope to remedy this starting as soon as I can get there on foot and stay for hours and discover the trails I've heard so many good things about but have yet to experience them myself. As for the new residents of Lincoln and surrounding areas make it a point to see the beautiful plants and ponds and the kids will love to visit the nature center and walk through the where the buffalo and the other large animals have a great habitat, very natural not like a zoo or anything. I plan on going tomorrow actually and I am going to try to get pictures of everything and then some. There's also an outdoor amphitheatre in the park and the shows are going on almost every weekend during the summer! Pioneers Park is a must visit with yourself and your pets or the whole family including the pets of course! Please don't forget the outdoor rule "You pack it in, you have to pack it out" there are trash bins everywhere if you are looking for one.
Beautiful and big park in Lincoln! Excellent place for walks (there are some trail options), taking photos and spending time with family and friends. Definitely worth your time!

name: University of Nebraska State Museum - Morrill Hall
address: Morrill Hall, 645 N 14th St, Lincoln, NE 68588, USA
reviews: We have come here a couple times with the family it has always been very enjoyable and educational. My kids love seeing the huge mammoths. My oldest son who loves animals loved seeing all the different kinds they had around the whole museum.  My dad and my son enjoyed looking at the varies rocks displayed on the second floor. There are so many different types of rocks to look at and a hands on science exhibit. The new exhibit on the third floor is really awesome as well. The kids got to do some hands on learning which was pretty great. Overall would highly recommend. The only downside might be parking but there is a parking garage close by and we just had to take a short walk to the museum.

The museum isn't open for many hours, but it was VERY enjoyable! They had many different topics, from the Nebraska plains to ancient fossils. They had many different interactive exhibits as well, so I 100% recommend this place for small children. I also went to the planetarium, and while it was enjoyable, I think it is more suited for young children. They have a very extensive collection, and the amount of information in there is extensive and thorough. Another really cool thing in there was the lab where they were opening casts of fossils on display. The entire facility was very clean, and the bathrooms looked a little old, but also clean. The bathrooms were a little weird to find, but not bad. Overall, I highly recommend this place if you are a fan of history and science for sure.

A neat museum and neat place to spend the afternoon. Lots to look at and explore. Some of the exhibits are very dated and could use some updates. 
Edit: I did visit the new fourth floor and it was great. Updates I would like to see would be better lighting. Many of the older exhibits are covered in shadow or very yellow light that makes it feel older and harder to see the exhibit.
What a great learning museum for the whole family! 4 floors of science and history of Nebraska and fossils galore! It's not pricey to get in and you and your kids will love it!
Lots of great learning experiences for kids and adults. Staff is friendly and helpful don't forget to ask for military discount if you are current or veteran for admission.

name: Museum of American Speed
reviews: These two Gentlemen gave us very nice tour. Only there for a few hours and it wasn't enough time. Racing history ,rare and important vehicles and auto related collections are packed into this large museum. The most amazing thing to me were the examples of ingenuity in vehicle and engine designs. If you like cars,racing, history or engineering go!

One of the best automotive museums I've been. Worth a couple of visits to study all the exhibit history or facts. 3 floor of memory, innovation and awesome collections of racing, hobby and American automotive lifestyle.

An absolutely stunning collection! Three floors of absolute heaven if you are a gear-head. Hundreds of cars, engines, pedal cars, toys, and other speed-related stuff. I spent three hours in there and I still didn't see it all. It's the kind of place where every time you visit, you will see something you hadn't seen before. Not only is there a lot of stuff to look at, but they constantly move things in and out to keep it fresh. Clean, well-maintained, excellent signage, and spot-on presentation of the collection. Not too many car museums are better than this one. A must visit spot for anyone into the subject!

Which words describes this place the best? Amazing? Fascinating? Awesome? Incredible? Magnificent? Mindblowing? Unique? Great? Cool? Well take all of these words and you have only 1% of what you will see!!! This museum rocks! It has so many cars, engines, models, part, toys ... you can spend here days (!!) not hours. There is so much to read, admire and discover that time flies by. There are three floors with tons of models in extraordinary shape. If you have fuel running through your veins you will cry when you see this place. I guess that it is one of the biggest car collections in the US. So many beautiful cars - simple incredible. The staff is very nice and friendly too, but be aware: They have much to tell. So if you ask a simple question you get the history of the car - which is simply fantastic! Great job by all the people working there. Thank you for the incredible day. Highly recommended!!!
This is an incredible collection. If you are a car buff this is a must visit.

name: Holmes Lake Park
address: 70th & Normal, S 70th St, Lincoln, NE 68506, USA
reviews: Very beautiful scenery. A place to relax and enjoy the sunshine and spend time with your family and friends. You can even swim and play with your dog at Holmes Lake Park. Great place to be for good times.

Whoever it was who set aside these lands for a park was a genius! Our family continues to love being at this park. The views of the lake are very stunning and it's just right there in the middle of town! The addition of gravel walking/running paths a few years ago made the park even more enjoyable and you can run/ bike there from many of the excellent bike paths. Walk around the lake on a maintained path, enjoy the children's park, watch a softball game or go fishing. Much to do and enjoy. You can watch the waterfowl and may even catch a glimpse of a fox.
This holds many memories for our family lots of laughs and smiles where I trained for my first marathon
This is a beautiful staple of Lincoln for all to enjoy.  Opportunities to bird watch, take an enjoyable stroll, or bike around the lake.

If you're looking for a nice place for an evening stroll or to take in the sunset, this is one of the best in Lincoln. It's a flood prevention lake built by the Army Corps of Engineers surrounded by a city park. There's a walking/biking loop, playgrounds, fishing and boating, baseball fields, sand volleyball, a small observatory, picnic shelters and plenty of ducks and geese to watch. Swimming is not allowed except during special events. If you're looking for a place to camp or do more aquatic activities, check out Branched Oak Lake instead. But if you're just looking for a place to exercise, relax, or just get away from life, Holmes Lake is a great choice.

name: Sheldon Museum of Art
address: 12th and R streets on the campus of the University of, Lincoln, NE 68508, USA
reviews:
Excellent Museum. Well curated and focused collection. Ken was so welcoming and just a wonderful docent who discussed the exhibits with us extensively. The museum building itself is really neat architecturally. We really enjoyed our time there.
The other "security" guy was a little rude and overbearing...Couldn't give me even 30 seconds to look at a painting because they had just closed (Not exaggerating I promise). Please let him know that when people take the time in their travels to come to your museum from out of town and donate admission...I think it's ok to behave friendly and give them an extra 60 seconds beyond closing time. In fact everything and everyone else was great so maybe that guy just needs a little softening up.
Seriously amazing. Great helpful staff in the front. And constant rotating and changing collections that they have on display.
The building is nice and the staff are friendly but the art collection is really small and the stuff they have on display aren’t that interesting, except for the bulls

As a Lincolnite, the Sheldon is a wonderful place to immerse yourself into art pieces from around the world. Whether it's a stroll through the sculpture garden or an adventure through the gallery, you won't be disappointed!

Went to a First Friday event at the Sheldon Museum. The building is beautiful & don't forget to take a walk around the outside to see some of the sculptures. The staff were enthusiastic plus they had a nice little buffet of snacks & drinks. Also liked how they had activities for children. It's a quick trip through this museum but fun for a family as well as a solo visit if you're in downtown Lincoln or on campus. Also liked the different types of art work that were displayed. The permanent as well as the feature exhibit were definitely different.

name: Nebraska State Capitol
reviews: The art is amazing, and I was really impressed with what they did with it. It’s not like normal capitols, most capitols are dome shaped but this goes strait up. I also like the inside. The art and engravings were just amazing. Also the tours were great. The tour guide talked about all the designs and art and gave a back story to all of it. Overall I had a good experience

We love visiting capitols and were impressed with  Nebraska’s. This building has tons of character and art work, friendly staff and beautiful architecture. The view from the observation level is awesome! The tour guide had lots of information.
The history behind this State Capital building was very interesting and informative.

Another capitol building, another stamp!  We made a stop here during our return road trip.  
We made our way up to the observation floor and there were a couple of doors leading outside that were open (inspections were being done and some construction/repairs so some areas were inaccessible). There are some nice views and so far this is the only state capitol building we visited that allowed visitors to step outside (North Dakota use to but some unruly teens caused that practice to end).  This building had a chain link fence type of cover over the gaps on the outside which is probably why they could allow folks to go out and enjoy the view.
The first floor allows you to make a bit of a circuit (because of the construction we couldn't actually do a full circuit so back tracked just a bit). There's plenty to see, even a bashful bust that hides behind a newspaper! 😁 He does have a face, I just had never seen a bust holding a paper so just had to take a photo (in a few years kids probably will need to ask what he's holding in his hands).

It was a random trip. We traveled to Lincoln to buy a car. Walked the streets that are lined in a perfect grid. While the tall building is a marvel, the treasure lies inside, dim light, spectacular tall beams, peerless marble work, wall murals, prefect chandeliers, the state house chambers, it has an imposing peaceful and quiet gravitas. The interplay of architecture, light and muted displays create a harmonious experience. The building is the museum. A must see.

name: International Quilt Museum
address: 1523 N 33rd St, entrance off 33rd, not, Holdrege St, Lincoln, NE 68503, USA
reviews: Man, I didn't even know that I liked quilts! I came here on a day trip with family, and it was fun getting to see the quilts and learning about all the work that goes into them. Definitely a must-visit if you have a couple hours and want to learn about something new!

Beautiful museum! Made it there 20 min to close and was able to see almost everything but in a rather rushed pace. I would recommend more like an hour to see it nicely. Staff was so nice too. I also recommend getting a Groupon we saved alot of money and I think it's available all the time.

Wonderful collection of traditional and contemporary quilts. Well done galleries for each type and exhibits change frequently.  A  treat to see the button quilt and the two sided Japanese quilt exhibit.

I expected the museum to be larger, but I think it's actually the perfect size to be able to enjoy without getting overwhelmed. I was grateful for the wheelchairs provided, which made it much easier for the whole family to enjoy. My only critique is I wish they had evening hours.

My wife is the quilting junkie: I just provide moral support (and woodworking support as needed).  But I very much enjoyed this museum.  We both thought it was an outstanding representation of a wide variety of quilts from around the world.  The facility is beautiful and spacious and very elderly and handicapped friendly.  Parking is on location, free, and spacious.
The arrangement of quilts by exhibit rooms allows the visitor to digest the intricate complexities of quilting by global region.  I particularly enjoyed the colorful quilts from India: they are breathtaking.  This is a must see even if quilting is really "not your thing."  You are sure to be impressed.

name: Nebraska History Museum
address: 131 Centennial Mall N, Lincoln, NE 68508, USA
reviews: Woah, there’s so much to learn from this museum. Short, detailed descriptions beside every exhibit are insightful.
This museum has a lot of valuable information and activities for children. This is a family trip. Great tourist attraction.
Well balanced collection with some Interesting and thoughtful displays.
Simple and accessible for a little time-killing walk-around
Super proud to visit the Women's Sufferage Exhibit! Good work NHM. 👧👩👵

name: National Museum of Roller Skating
reviews: A very unique and super cool museum of the history of Roller Skating. I was trying to figure out what the previous reviews meant by “don’t forget your quarters,” but after visiting I would say bring a quarter or two!

Very neat collection of roller skating memorabilia and equipment. However, the museum is located, quite strangely, in the rear of an office building. We wanted to buy something from the gift shop but there was hardly a soul in the whole building, and we had to grab someone from the cubicles to complete the transaction. Overall, just a kinda weird museum experience.

If you ever skated as a kid, you'll enjoy the museum. Who knew the first skates were inline? Apollo Ono and Tara Lipinski started on roller skates. Rhonda Cann, the director, is a wealth of additional information. And it's free with free parking. Well worth the time!

A long time ago my friend and I roller skating accross NYC, her using roller skates and me using roller blades,  Everytime I go to the museum it reminds me of more innocent days and our friendship. She passed on, so this is all i have left and the memories
Great little museum.  A must visit when in Lincoln

name: Wilderness Park
reviews: Cool place to go out and explore the edge of city wilderness. Vast array of flowering plants in the spring. Excellent place to go birding, see wildlife, ride your horse, bicycle, walk your dog or go on a nature y date. Also a good place to find inner solace and meditation on a self walk. Nice get away from the hustle and bustle of the city. Nice little stream, pleasantly bubbly. If walking in spring/summer, wear bug spray. The water is also a mosquito haven.
There are so many trails and so much space. The scenery is always beautiful, no matter which area you start at. I often see wildlife while I'm here and it's close to get to from home.
Beautiful area to take our dogs to get away from the sounds of the city a little. They loved it as much as we enjoyed the walk around!
True Wilderness trail. The trail is well marked. The creek cuts through the trail. The opportunity to explore the outdoor vegetation and animal pathways are undending. Our dog lived the trails.
Great place to get away from the city without going far

name: Lincoln Children's Zoo
reviews: My whole family just loves it here. I am so happy that they are open year round now. Price is affordable for such an amazing experience and sweet memories for the kids to look back. Thank you so much for your hard work and kindness. We, local people really appreciate your contribution.

I have been going to the Lincoln Children's Zoo now ever since I was a toddler myself. I've seen the Zoo change over the years. This recent additional growth has allowed the Zoo to grow and add many new items for people to see. They have a program with the Lincoln Public School to offer Zoo School. The Zoo has its own train and recently laid new track to replace the 30 year old track. They have a beautiful Zoo Gift shop and I now have been told that they have a new restaurant in the Zoo. I look forward to taking my nephew's this summer to the new and improved Lincoln Zoo.

This zoo is a great place to take kids as it is just the right size. The path through the zoo is very straightforward and kids usually seem to stay on the path. This makes managing your little ones easier! The Omaha zoo is a pretty cool place but I like the layout of the Lincoln zoo much better for smaller children. The new attractions are great (tigers, giraffes, red pandas, etc.) and the summer time brings a lot more volunteers to actually touch some of the animals. It's a great zoo for children.
A lot of the new animals and additions are great! It's a nice zoo for little kids. We have had fun exploring the different places and feeding some of the animals.

Disclosure, I haven't actually been to the zoo during normal operating hours...but did check it out for the first time last night for Zoo Lights & it was a fabulous experience! The event was well organized and put together & the lights were great! I will definitely be making a visit back to the zoo to check out all the exhibits & such! :)

name: Hazel Abel
reviews: A tiny park but a very compact and adorable parks! Definitely on my list of top 3 favorite parks in Nebraska! So many places for pictures and picnics with friends, family and pets! I highly recommend this park to photographers looking for locations in Lincoln for photoshoots! :)

I was so happy to see that the park was so well kept up when we were there, the maintenance and improvements done in the last few years really show. it is a great place to take pictures even though the neighborhood can be kind of rough. My girls had fun sticking their hands in the fountain and playing on the equipment and looking at all the pretty structures.
Small park in historic neighborhood with beautiful landscape and features.  Great place to take photos...senior pictures, etc.

Grew up here going to this park. 

Came back after 29 years away and took my daughter. 

Nothing like when i was a kid, but she still lived it
I got married here years ago.

name: Lux Center For the Arts
reviews: I haven't had the opportunity to visit for a class or anything, but my sister gave me a tour of the facility. A very nice little studio will all different art forms. Staff was friendly too.
Friendly and knowledgeable staff! Many surprising treasures in this gallery,  gift shop and arts center!
Lots of beautiful art. We went to family day and the kids learned a lot and had a lot of fun!
Wonderful art gallery and shop for locally made art, jewelry and more
Excellent gallery shows. High end and unique

name: Great Plains Art Museum
reviews: What a gem of a gallery! I'd never been there before and was so impressed by the artwork displayed! Two prairie chickens made entirely of cut pieces of paper and amazing paintings & poems in the basement (Art & Poetry of the Barada Hills) we're my favorites! Worth going!

Great displays of Great Plains art from a rotating group of artists. Varied literary collections from Great Plains historians.
It all starts out front with a mini sculpture garden that draws you in from the usual hustle of a University campus 
Walking through the doors into the several floors of galleries and special exhibits is truly a step back in time.

Located in downtown, I was surprised to see that there were no reviews. So I figured I would pop in and see why. And to tell you, I don't know why. This is a small but interesting art collection and is well worth at least an hour of art appreciation.Some excellent American artists on display here including Frederic Remington (I've seen his sculptures in many places, including Bismarck and Salt Lake City), John Falter, Albert Bierstadt and Edwin Deming. The display of stereoscopes was super cool and having a device there to actually look through was awesome.

I LOVE the Great Plains Art Museum! They always have amazing shows up, with their impressive library just up the stairs. Not to mention they’re right downtown, just across from the bus stop, and are only a quick jaunt to the Haymarket. Highly recommend!!

We attended a special symposium last week "Epic Neihardt". The staff was welcoming and helpful. The Art Museum is lovely and easy to navigate. The layout (bathroom in the basement level) worked well for this event. Take a tour on your lunch break if you work downtown or on campus. Some great visual art (Sculpture) greets you upon arrival the entrance is on the east side of Hewit Place. Spend some time here and get to know The Great Plains!

name: Larsen Tractor Museum
address: N 35th St & Fair St, Lincoln, NE 68583, USA
reviews: This was a cool place to see. The staff is very informative about the transformation of tractors over the last century.

Nebraska Jewel 💎 
Agricultural Prism 🚜
Free Family Fun 👍

Well this is definitely another unique Museum to be added to the list of y'all ain't going to believe there's a museum to do this list. This Museum Chronicles what has happened over the last 100 years with tractors being tested so that one can determine if the claims of the manufacturer and the performance of the tractor are equal. It turns out that Nebraska took this so seriously that in order to sell a tractor in Nebraska it's got to be certified and it's performance of its duties. I was lucky enough to come during the time when there was no crowd of students only the staff at the Museum. The lady who was the executive director had a script that was memorized that told stories of the tractors and the history of the testing and why it became important and how it's recognized now worldwide, it's an incredible story.
Interesting  our speaker  was very good answered  all questions showed us around we also watched  a CD
Awesome place to see the progression of farm equipment and tractors .

name: St Mary's Catholic Church
reviews: What this church lacks in appearance it really makes up for in passion of the priests and service to the poor and ill.  Loved spending time there.
Nice church and people and food net

Very nice place. The first time I'd been in there (for memorial service). It was a nice, clean, welcoming environment. There was lots of space. Lots of metered parking since it's right down town. Just depends on the day of the week and the time of the day how available parking will be.
My St Mary's church is wonderful place to pray and give thanks to the Lord.
So beautiful! A peaceful, prayerful place.

name: Hyde Observatory Holmes Park
reviews: I've gone to this observatory for years.  My son's liked going when they were young too.  You'll fall even more in love w the stars after looking through the telescopes.  They put on nice shows for adults and older children.

They have multiple telescopes that you can look through and several fascinating videos on space that are shown every week. It's a good date idea of you're looking for something other than "dinner and a movie" and don't mind letting your inner nerd shine. You might want to check the forecast before hand though. If it's drizzling, they won't expose the telescopes but they will still show a video or two and have people there who can answer many of your astronomy questions.

went there and they were closed due to winter hours :*( saddest moment of my life. really enjoy the architecture, however. Holmes lake is beautiful at 8 pm.  would've gotten a full 5 if they were open
Awesome volunteer staff. Great conversation and very knowledgeable
A great place to visit.  Open every Saturday night.

name: The Veterans Memorial Garden
address: 3200 Veterans Memorial Dr, Lincoln, NE 68502, USA
reviews: Serine place to reflect and give thanks to our veterans. The different dedications are written in large lettering making it easy to see which branch of the military or which war the memorial is representing. The walking path is calm and I found it was a good place to teach my son about what our military has done in the past and how he can pay proper respects.

Very Nice. Lots of names and history to see. Great place to start teaching kids about the sacrifices so many Americans have made. Wish some of the monuments were better updated or taken care of. It's hard in the city to maintain I know. Most we pretty cool.
Great place for remembering our Veterans.
A quiet place to reflect on lost loved ones and people that fought for what they believed in. GPS game friendly,just be respectful.
Beautiful Veterans Memorial. I Walk My Dog Almost Everyday And See This Garden.

name: Licorice International Haymarket
reviews: Amazing selection! Great prices! I’m obsessed with salty licorice and it’s impossible to find stores that sell the kinds I like! This store has it all and they are super fast with shipping orders! Shipping is not absurd either!
This was the #1 destination on our list for our first trip to Nebraska. It was 1000x worth it!!! So many different licorice from many countries. We will definitely be coming back!!

You can guess what they sell licorice all kinds of licorice very strong wish licorice from various countries and large assortment and you can try all the samples you want They also have some unique candies and candy bars from around the US
Lovely place! The owners were wonderful and there is a huge assortment of licorice and candy.  Seriously, it's probably the best candy/licorice store I've ever visited

Great services for the Gift I wished to create. They are moving and expanding.
Union College, 4725 Prescott Ave  & Haymarket, 230 N.  7th St

name: Holmes Lake Park
address: Holmes Lake Parking Lot, 3, Holmes North Shore Rd, Lincoln, NE 68506, USA
reviews: Diverse groups of people. Walking path around the entire lake. Benches and picnic tables. Kids play area. Covered picnic areas. Fishing.

Lovely crushed limestone to run/walk on and such beautiful scenery as you go around the lake. I love hearing the birds, spotting different varieties and watching the waterfowl along the way. Great kayak spot also and always smiling faces. If you need motivation to get a workout in, this is the spot!

Huge space with lots of opportunities to get close up to the water! Bring your non-motorized watercraft water board, canoe or kayak whatever & there's plenty of walking or biking trails. There's benches spread out throughout the park and picnic areas available. Great outdoor playground area for the kids!

Great place to bring your family to relax or just come solo and watch the sunset over the lake. The locals know about the back entrance you gonna have to go and find it yourself. Look for the star observatory.
Simply breathtaking sunsets. Jogging, bike trails, perfect place for open air business meetings, or moments of solitude. Must see this park. Bring the kids and enjoy.

name: Mahoney Park
reviews: Good park, with alot of activities and open space. It's right in the middle of lincoln so you are surrounded by homes and can see a view of walmart over the horizon.

This park is a nice peaceful place to bring the family or even have a nice party at. There is a playground for the children, as well as a tennis court and basketball court. Further into the park is a baseball field. It's beautiful nature is best seen during the summer months when all the trees are in full bloom!
So pretty and plenty to do. Great park!
The park is a great place to just chill and hang out with your babies and get away
Beautiful park. Well maintained. Nice, paved trail.

name: Trago Park
address: N 22nd St & U St, Lincoln, NE 68503, USA
reviews: Fun!!! As always!! Children of all ages have fun and you can even see some of the adults getting into the fun!! There's more than just the splash pad. There's a small playground and swings for those who want to take a break from the water but not the fun! There are a few rope sculptures that can be climbed on and into. Great fun for everyone!!!

Loved this park! My children enjoyed the play equipment as well as the walking trail. It was clean and we loved the cute little tables and stumps etc. carved from stone! My 15 year old son did find a suitcase with what appeared to have a homeless persons belongings inside. ( he opened it before my husband or I could stop him!) There was also someone sleeping in plain sight right in the bushes on the other end of the park... at 3:30 in the afternoon! The couple asleep in the bushes didn't bother us though, and if there are other homeless people staying in this park, they clean up after themselves and don't leave trash laying around. Really neat little spot overall!
Very nice lil spot for a hot lil day

Why do I love this park? It's FREE! You can spend the afternoon or just stop to cool off real quick on a hot summer day. Picnic tables, shaded benches for reading, basket ball court, spray park and it's all right next to a beautiful bike trail.
Nice park close to UNL and downtown area. The splash park is a fun summer activity for young and old alike.

name: Stransky Park
address: 17th St & Harrison Avenue, Lincoln, NE 68502, USA
reviews: Stopped at this cute little park while we were in Lincoln. Water area and water fountain was empty / turned off which makes since it's just now warming up. Very clean, kids loved the equiptment, and going up the stairs to the waterfall area. Smaller then I expected but plenty of room to play. No restroom.
Tons of kids messing around and throwing things. The music was pretty good though.

wonderful little park with a little something for everybody. Nice green spaces, a beautiful waterfall, a small children's play area and some nice footpaths. All in a quiet neighborhood, with available parking.

This is a beautiful park! It's well taken care of, always clean, and tucked away in a quiet neighborhood. The rock waterfall in my opinion, is the prettiest in the city. Great place to go with family or if you need a peaceful spot to clear your mind.
A tiny park that's five times the fun and adventure!

name: Tierra Briarhurst Park
reviews: I absolutely love walking these trails. The environment is beautiful and there is so much wildlife to observe. There are several deer, tons of fox and lots of squirrels. I do wish other people would respect the area and not leave trash around. This trail allows easy access to Russ's Market and the 33rd and highway 2 area as well as Tierra Park and connects to several other trails.

The hubs plays disc golf here. I bring a dog or two and we tag along. Walking the dogs at Tierra Briarhurst Park is pretty painless. You can walk the trail or off-road it, which is what we usually do. The trails have exercise stops if you are into that kind of thing. The dogs mainly sniff the equipment. After that they aren't interested.
Family friendly and also dog friendly. A great place to get lost talking pictures.
Nice park. Caught a 19"bass in the run off.... And a few others.
Plenty of room for multiple people. Clean and maintained facilities.

name: Star City Shores
reviews: Godchild's swim meet this morning. Never been to this facility before. Beautiful grounds, clean and well maintained. Pools we're crystal clear. Plenty of room for participants and spectators. Had a chance to visit with several employees, life guards - very polite and engaging.

This is my over all favorite of all of the City pools. Its not just a typical "public pol," it's a mini water park. This particular pool is really great for the smaller kids and the ones not quite swimming yet as there is a large playset in the shallows giving them a lot of activity. There is also a nice, covered wading place to sit with your infant or toddler. It walks down, much like the beach so it is easy for anybody to get in and out of. Lastly, the last day of the year that the pool is open is "dogs day" where you can bring your dog...however I hear you need to get your pooch his ticket early as they limit the amount of dogs.
Very Nice place
Bathroom and restroom are dirty and old. Need to take care and clean more often.
Seems to be really busy all the time but kids have lots of fun.

name: Deer Springs Winery
reviews: This is a great venue for music. Shaded lawn. Easy drive from Omaha and Lincoln. Some delicious reds and whites reasonably priced.

First of all, if you enjoy wine (even a little bit), I suggest taking a day trip doing tastings at the many wineries around the Lincoln metro. I've found that each region of the US has a unique wine culture and Nebraska is no different. Deer Springs would be a great stop on a day tour. It's located in a cute little house on a nice green space. There's a patio and gazebo area for outdoor seating.I'd recommend a tasting of the wines. They have a variety of reds and whites that range from dry to sweet. Like other Nebraska wineries, they tend toward the sweeter spectrum but that's our local viniculture (the types of grapes that grow in the region).
Very good wine and entertainment on the weekends.

The entire experience is always EXCELLENT. The wines are, in my opinion, the best around. The staff is always friendly and very knowledgeable. And the ambiance is lovely. From the restored farmhouse with the cozy fireplace and tables where you do your tastings, to the outside areas...firepit...gazebo...it's just so relaxing. And when they have music...you can be assured it is also the best around. Highly recommend!
So peaceful, quiet, enjoying, friends......Today was an amazing day spent with my friend for my birthday!

name: James Arthur Vineyards
address: 2001 W Raymond Rd, Raymond, NE 68428, USA
reviews: Great place for a "corporate" vineyard. They have live music, great outside seating areas, good wine sample tasting options. The area is really beautiful and it has a very relaxing atmosphere. It can be rather busy though on some weekend afternoons but they have plenty of help so getting served doesn't take long.

This vineyard had cats. That's an A+ from me. 

(Good wine too)
Great place, excellent wine and atmosphere.

Delicious wines and now hard apple cider. We try to go out there at least once a year to try the new products and re-sample the other items. You can get cheese, bread, and a meat product with a wine pasting. Our favorite is Edyn's Blush.
An experience we'd recommend to everyone!

name: Memorial Stadium
address: One Memorial Stadium Drive, Lincoln, NE 68588, USA
reviews:
Although getting to the stadium is a long walk from parking lot 19, it is well worth.  I have been to all Big 10 football stadiums and this was the best experience.   The Nebraska fans are the best.  Very welcoming and kind.  Plus the University's football tradition makes attending a game a real great experience. 
The red out lights they do between quarters was fantastic.
Thanks Nebraska fans!

If you are a college football fan, you need to attend a game in Lincoln.  The fans are amazing and take pride it welcoming the other team.  It is located close to downtown Lincoln so there are options to traditional tailgating.  This is an old school stadium.  I do recommend getting the seats because of the bench’s.  It gets tight.  Go Big Red.

We are from Oklahoma. I thought the workers would be kinder, but I get it, they are busy. I would definitely go back. And the bathrooms are clean. I also like how you can load your own hot dog, as I like lots of mustard. :) Go Huskers!

First time for me and was a pretty good experience. Was there with my lady who is a Husker Fan and me I am from Wisconsin so go Badgers. 37-21 Badgers awesome. Was in section 32 row 98 way way up and would have been nice except for the 20mph wind blowing right in our direction. Loved the stadium and the prices for things very reasonable compared to other stadiums that's for sure. Will definitely be going again.
We love watching the football games here as a family! The atmosphere on game day Saturday’s is amazing.

name: Cripple Creek Park
reviews: Such a great time there with my kids. There is not shortage of play structures for them to climb around on

This park is super lame. The great, colorful jungle gym and slides in some of the posted photos are part of the elementary school next door. There was no divider between the two areas, which made it hard to determine where my little could play. We happened to go during recess, so we avoided the places where school kids were, which was literally all of the cool stuff. My recommendation would be not to go during a school day.

We live in the neighborhood and absolutely enjoy relaxing atmosphere of the park. It is not too big and just enough people/activities. The park is next to the school and includes the soccer field ( I saw people practicing baseball as well).
Nice park for kids of all ages. Sidewalks around the playground area so children can ride scooters or bikes.  Slides, swings, trees to climb. Small covered picnic shelter area.
Great little park to take the family to.

name: Bill Harris Iron Horse Park
reviews: Went to the farmer's market (Saturday mornings through Oct.)- they have (almost) everything! Goat cheese from Dutch Girl Creamery, jam from Lana's Jams & Jellies, and amazing up-cycled goods from Marjorie Mae. For those that love the food carts, there were tons of baked goods & snack items, along with burritos or pulled pork. And of course the fresh produce & lots of craft items and great gift ideas. I recommend getting there early for parking though...
If you love trains you will love it, small park with an original steam locomotive an a car. Nice!
I love the train and the the brick art definitely an interesting part of the hay market.
Nice park in the middle of town.
Nice aesthetic addition to this area. Would be a great place for a walk.

name: American Historical Society of Germans From Russia
reviews: Rich in history. Germans from Russia that immigrated here to Lincoln. They have artifacts, instruments and a blacksmith shop, a church. Even a store, & outbuildings. Quite unique. My ancestors are from Prussia so I may be a little bias.

OK, who even knew that "Germans From Russia" was even a Thing?? Much less that they even have their own museum?! Well, if my own grandfather had not actually been one, and a homesteading immigrant to boot, I would be included among the vast number of ignoranti myself. Stop in and give this delightful little tribute to an obscure but interesting historical niche a visit and then head down to Beatrice to the Homestead Monument for broader context.
Visited the open house. Great history. Very friendly people.

Sneaky stuff.  I had been there before and I missed 90 percent of it.  They have a 20 min. video that explains why they left Russia.  In it is a picture of the Havelock Shops in a building where they were constructing train steam engines.  I lived across from there for 34 years and I had not seen that picture before.  Most of the displays are on the second floor of the main building.   In the basement is a research library.  In the back are several more buildings.  Unfortunately they are seasonly closed until April.  There is a chapel, general store, blacksmith shop and a couple more buildings.
Great place to visit visit your heritage.

name: Branched Oak State Recreation Area
address: 12000 W Branched Oak Rd, Raymond, NE 68428, USA
reviews: This time of year is magnificent at Branched Oak. Today there were so many snow geese and some bald eagles. Such a sight to behold plus the sound of all those snow geese is etched in my mind forever. Thank you Jesus for such beauty!

Very large lake. Great for boating and big groups. We have my bf's company picnic there every summer. Very popular lake because pretty close to Lincoln and Omaha. On site dump station...bathrooms and showers...swim area. Very populated though during the season.

This is a nice park. The lake is beautiful. The only downside is if you go here on any sort of holiday during the summer, be prepared to feel like a sardine. The camper sites are extremely close to each other. So you're going to get to see your neighbor's quite a bit, whether you want to or not.
Nice clean camping grounds. Non- residents pay 8$ per night. Park was well maintained and situated on a very nice lake. Was raining so did not get to enjoy as much as I would have liked.
A great lake for families and your furry little friends. Also a great place to take beautiful pictures.

name: Eugene T. Mahoney State Park
address: 28500 W Park Hwy, Ashland, NE 68003, USA
reviews: This place is awesome! Some friends were staying at a cabin there. The cabin was very nice, multiple bedrooms a full kitchen, full dining room table, a large spacious home. The kids played at the activity center with huge tubes and tunnels for the jungle gym. There is a rock climbing facility and ice skating rink right there. They had a sledding hill out back of the activity center with artificial snow machine. The other play grounds around the park were great as well. Very cool place, take your kids no matter the age they will love it!

Very nice state park! They have super reasonable indoor climbing and ice skating!  The rock wall is pretty cool, they have top rope, lead, and bouldering.  They have quite a few auto belays and 42-foot walls!  The ice skating rink looked nice, too.  I'd love to hike the observation deck there, but it is closed until Fall 2020 for repair they said. Will definitely be going back there!

We found this park while traveling on I-80 to Omaha. Beautiful area and looks like a great family vacation spot! Pool, zip line, lookout tower hiking trails, cabins, lodge, restaurant. Other places of interest nearby. Open year around!

Parks good, kids love the playgrounds, trials and mini golf. They need to move to a more traditional form of walk-up space reservation. They make you drive around, find your place and stop by the front to reserve before dropping your trailer which may or may not still be available. Most allow you to drop your camper and than pay. Much easier and less likely to trip over others.

We visited the indoor playground and had a blast.  Very affordable for what you get.  There are many places for parents to sit while the kids run around and you can even order Valentino's pizza or other snacks to eat.

name: Porter Park
reviews: Nice little lunch spot for the family to picnic

Good good park to play in I took my kids they loved it I don't see any reason why no one else wouldn't love this park I had son brought the dog do the frisbee no one lingering around like weird parks.
Cool park 👍
Great neighborhood playground with nice slides, swings and a basketball court.
Good park for younger kids with imaginations.

name: SCHRAMM PARK STATE RECREATION AREA
reviews: Beautiful hiking large fish to watch even the geese were fun I know more than a park sticker it was a day of family enjoyment

Very pretty and peaceful. It was early Spring so the full beauty of the plants and trees was still emerging.  Do note that this is a Nebraska State Park, so buy a pass before going, or you will need to pay when you get there. The drive to the Park was nice too.
Such a wonderful place! Beautiful trails and plenty to do!

A wonderful place to spend the day with family and friends. Numerous activities for children and a fun way to learn about Nebraska. Featuring many fish, birds, plants and wildlife native to Nebraska. Walking and biking trails and beautiful  scenic river views. Schramm park is beautiful any time of year.
This place is pretty great for hiking! We do the 3 mile loop, which has variation with ups and downs. The scenery is pretty and the trail is well marked! Would definitely recommend!!

name: Strategic Air Command & Aerospace Museum
address: 28210 W Park Hwy, Ashland, NE 68003, USA
reviews:
Awesome museum with both aircraft and rockets. 

I had the advantage of coming here with my son, an airman with the USAF, who is knowledgeable with just about every aircraft on display. They are decommissioned planes and some you get the chance to see the innards - a plus. The facility from both the outside and in is super clean and impressive to behold. And as an added bonus they also have a space-related display from NASA as well as a tribute to fallen airmen from 911 and the missions that followed. 

I highly recommend coming here and paying a visit.

The place is a decent museum to take your children. Especially if they're interested in airplanes or rocket ships. They have a nice children's learning area. I have only two issues with this museum. One, it's far out of the way from the Omaha metro area. Two, a lot of things could use to be updated here. There's lots of dust on all the aircraft. And the exhibits are pretty outdated, but still fun.

Really enjoyed the visit here.  The SR-71 Blackbird on display is visible when you walk in the door and is very impressive.  I think my favorite display was the MIG-21 which is kind of hidden in a corner.  I also thought the Hobgoblin experimental fighter was an excellent display.  This museum has one of only two that were ever produced.

The activity centers for the kids are very good.  All of the activities are science based and created opportunites to explain science concepts to the kids.

This place is awesome! Of course the SR-71 is the big draw and was awesome! They have a B-52 , and many many more pieces of aviation history. The personal items that belonged to Gary Powers was neat. Next time I’m in the area I’ll definitely stop back! Anyone that has any interest in aviation or space wont be disappointed.

A few years ago I toured the United States Air Force Strategic air command Museum and found it to be a great museum to take family and friends to. My father who was a former SAC member would have love to visit this great museum.The museum is staffed by an excellent staff for volunteers with knowledge of all the military exhibits and the history of Strategic Air Command . Great Tour

name: Platte River State Park
reviews: So beautiful and well kept. My kids had so much fun exploring and having a little adventure! Would highly recommend coming and visiting this amazing state park!
Valentine's Dinner was great. I had the buffalo. The rolls are super soft with cinnamon butter on them. I could make that a meal. Had to take food home as I was stuffed.

Beautiful park. I stayed in one of the cabins with a school group. There was plenty of room in our cabin. There is one big bed on one side and two bunk bed sets on the other side. The park is nice and clean. Fishing is good and the paddle boats were a favorite of ours.

6$ to get in lots to explore! We used it for a photoshoot with a mermaid since they have a waterfall. The waterfall was a little busy but all really nice people! They have easy medium and hard trails and the front desk was very helpful to show us where the waterfall was. You can also rent cute cabins! Also horse rentals!
Nebraska’s treasure. One of my favorite places to spend time. The falls are beautiful as always. Missed the horses, hope they return soon.

name: Lincoln Children's Museum
reviews: There were interesting exhibits and play areas here. Our son at the time was probably a bit young (about 2) to fully experience all the activities, we spent most our time playing with the large you trucks they had and at the foam brick play area. The cost was a bit much, since it was my wife and I taking our one child.

Such a fun place!!  My daughter loves it!!  It's very clean, and there is a large variety of different activities for many age groups. The staff is very friendly and helpful. We drove from Omaha and it was worth it. This was our second visit and we will be back soon.

A bit pricey for three people, but a great environment for the little ones. Lots of learning opportunities and all of the exhibits are built for exploration. Areas are also spacious enough to allow parents to play with their kids. Does get a bit busy! The also have a super cute wall of all the contributors and partners!

We love the place.. but so many of the activities are broken.. or missing everything.. it is clean enough.. and the kids still have fun.. just wish things were better maintained.. and it is very expensive

Fun interactive play for all age groups. Multiple professions,  rooms and activities.  You can easily spend 3 hours with your littles. The place is clean and organized.  It makes a great family activity.

name: Fun-Plex Waterpark & Rides
reviews: A great place to take the smaller children. Other than the go cart track and water features there's not many rides for the kids older than 13. My grandchildren always have fun. But my 15 yr old grandson gets bored quickly.
A great place to spend a day! Maybe a little pricey, but we have so much fun. The big waterslides are fantastic and they have smaller ones for the little kiddos too, so all ages are covered.

Fun plex is a great place to enjoy an afternoon with the family.  Is it six flags, no but for a small park, we always have a good time.  Funplex sells season passes at a discount online as a black Friday deal.
We had a blast on July 4! Riding go karts and water slides was great!! It is a safe place to have some outdoor without losing track of your group. Got here at 11am & had very short waits.
Great place to go an spend a day relaxing and having fun with the family!! Amusement rides were great, staff very friendly, wasn't overcrowded, something for everyone. Cant wait to go back!

name: Lincoln Fire & Rescue,
reviews: Cool museum. The Fire station staff were great, well informed and good with our toddler.
Small but really nice museum of fire & rescue history. Thank you very much for the day on fire station 1

This is a great little museum! Our tour guide was one of the female firefighters. She was top notch! She explained everything that was used in the past, then escorted my wife, her parents, and myself out to the new trucks they have and showed us their new equipment. It was so interesting, my family talked about it for about an hour during our lunch down the street at Wendy's. 

We visited on a Saturday morning so, we did not get to see the administration office or meet any of the administration staff but, we still had a great time. It was a perfect little get-away while we were visiting the city for a family reunion.

I would plan for about an hour tour. It depends on how many questions are asked by your group members. Keep in mind this museum is located in an active fire station and your guide can be called out at any moment.
Love The Museum,  a Great facility to visit and you can learn so much about the history of Lincoln Fire and Firefighting.   Thanks.
A room of old fire stuff.

name: Holy Family Shrine
reviews: I've seen it many times from the interstate and finally went up there today. It's such a beautiful place! Besides looking at the shrine you can also take a walk around it and look at the story of Jesus Christ and his crucifixion. It's a really lovely and calm place in general.

Simply gorgeous, peaceful and serene. I've driven past this church on the interstate many times, but never took the time to stop and didn't really know how to get there. Eventually, took the drive and used Google Maps to easily navigate, which I highly suggest you do, as well. Nothing but pure beauty and calm await. There are initial out buildings and gift shop, which I didn't know about. There's also a water feature which stems all the way inside the chapel. You can read the entire story as to why and the vision which inspired this wonderful design into reality. Such a beautiful story for a beautiful Nebraska landmark! Check it out, even if you're not Catholic!
Awesome place to visit as a guest or spiritual retreat fro Omaha.  Just off the same exit as the outlets.

Such a beautiful and serene place to be! Travelers are able to take in the beauty of the majestic land around, as they sit and meditate or pray in peace. The area offers beautiful views and wonderful landscaping. A person may come in, and feel comfortable knowing they belong there.

Great visit and definitely worth stopping for.  Wonderful story and beautiful building and grounds. Staff was helpful but not overbearing.  Being able to roam and enjoy everything as we wanted was perfect.

name: OPPD Arboretum
reviews: It is a great place to take a walk in town and still see some nature.  I think it is wonderful OPPD took the time to make this place and not just leave a large white grave field with electrical equipment.

OPPD Arboretum is a place you would love to go when you wanna stretch a little bit. It has that bit of beautiful naturistic assemble in the middle of the chaos. I went on the first day of spring to there, but I think wasn't the wisest decision. The place would be more beautiful with all the green fronds developing over a month from now. Maybe that would bar the constant noise from the adjoining street. I'll go once more, later in summer to see how things unfold there.

This is a gorgeous park! Amazing for photos. Would definitely be prepared for waiting in line if you’ll be visiting for photoshoots. In the 8-10 times I’ve been here there has always been an overly saturated amount of photographers taking photos here 15-30.
My children and I love coming here in any weather!  There's a beautiful little hill with boulders at the top that we love going to, pretending we have our own little mountains in Omaha.

Great place for family pictures! Plenty of variety in trees, nice windy pathways and benches. There is even an easily walked dirt path through the thick grove. It can be a bit of a feeding frenzy for photographers around sunset and on the weekends, but everyone I've met were pleasant and helpful in  allowing each other space.

name: Standing Bear Lake
reviews: This is a nice place to go for a walk with and without your dogs. I would give it 5 stars if the paths on both sides of the lake were connected.
This place is fantastic, my wife and I visited to go on a run as we are pretty new to the area, and loved it. They have a little bit of everything here!!

Wonderful path for walking with children! It has lots of foot and bike traffic, but the path is designed for it and wide enough for everyone. Alternately shaded and sunny for all weather. We did not see any benches or picnic tables, but we didn't walk all the way around.
Nice lake.  Pretty good fishing.  Too much littering.

Really love this area. We live withing walking distance and it is awesome to walk on the trails. My only complaint is I wish the trail connected all the way around the lake! Once you reach 144th street it is unfortunate to turn around instead of make a loop around the lake. It is a great place to Kayak as well!

name: Lauritzen Gardens/Kenefick Park
reviews:
Beautiful! Way bigger than you expect! 

Because of the weather... Guess what, most plants are dead. However, the set up and design of the garden grounds were so mesmerizing that you almost don't need any plants!! 

I expected to stay 1 hour, but actually-- I stayed 3 hours! This place is so beautiful and well kept. Very much worth the $11 fee to enter.

Also, the place looks like only the building. Some other lady particular noted "what's outside?" "Oh, I think it's just a small path." ..... Think again!!!! Outside, the property is HUGE. Don't miss out on the outdoor portion.

Anyways, I recommend. I went alone, which is great, but it's also perfect for a date or bringing your kids or chatting with friends. Superb 🙂

This place is amazing! The lobby area and multi-level greenhouse are a fun quick visit in the winter (Christmas display, model trains, LEGO exhibits, etc.), and the outdoor area is an adventure to explore during nicer weather. 

The outdoor area includes a running model train exhibit (multiple tracks and trains) and you can spend an afternoon wandering around the gardens. You can also visit the real train engines near the entrance, and the gardens have an annual European car show out on the grounds.

Definitely check it out! It's worth your time.

The inside atrium is warm and inviting and colorful and has a huge variety of plants. I'm glad they label so many of the plants/trees. Fountains and brick work add so much to the experience. Very walkable/wheelchair-able. The outside is great for long walks - a lot to see. The tram is also a great choice, as they let you off - to walk around both the Founder's Garden & the Rose Garden.

There is so much to see!  We could have spent a lot longer here and we will definitely be back!  I highly recommend seeing the LEGO sculptures while they are there at Lauritsen Gardens.  The staff that we dealt with were all very polite and helpful.  We will be watching for future events and are considering a yearly membership even though we live 90 minutes away.

The Lauritzen Gardens isba great place to go and wonder around in the summer. They have lovely gardens and plenty of space to wonder through while enjoying the outdoors. They also have the Lego traveling exhibit that comes through every year and their lights at Christmas time are lovely as well.  Wear comfortable shoes!!

name: Pinnacle Bank Arena
address: 400 Pinnacle Arena Dr, Lincoln, NE 68508, USA
reviews: Very nice facility, easy to navigate around. Plenty of room and places for snacks or drinks. The only issue was parking which is expected. I didn't expect them to only except cash for state basketball. One ATM "out of service " 30 minutes later I find a ATM. Bring cash you'll be fine.

Wonderful facility that can host anything from a rock concert to a sporting events. Staff is courteous and helpful, everything is clean and reasonable comfortable. Some drawbacks are parking and concession prices but where isn’t that an issue?

Great experience, parking was close (although 10 bucks), walk from parking before and after the concert was well lit and safe. Staff inside were organized and professional, although nobody on security staff seemed to care that a 70 yr old dude in pancake makeup smashed a glittery guitar on stage while people egged him on. Also another 70 yr old guy wearing dragon boots, and playing a bass guitar was bleeding out of his mouth on stage and medical staff were NOWHERE to be found. At one point near the end, the backdrop burst into explosions, sparks and fire, it’s amazing nobody perished. The place was left with confetti paper everywhere, very disrespectful of my fellow concert goers to leave the place so messy. Other than these few small issues, overall was a very positive experience.
Great arena and comfortable seats! Made for a great high school state game day! Friendly staff as well when you are standing in the walkways waiting for seats.
Always been nice and clean whenever I have been here. Staff is very friendly and helpful. Great place for concerts and sports.

name: The Durham Museum
reviews: Love the history and the ambiance of the place. The soda fountain is pretty legit, too and isn't overly expensive. Go for a membership if you have a big family like us- you'll save money the second time you come. Sometimes younger kids may not have the attention span to really get into like older kids and adults.

Nice place to learn about Omaha and Nebraska's history.  This older train station has full size locomotives indoors that you can walk through.  Well worth the $8 fee. Perfect for a 2 hour tour before getting back on plane.  Is only 10 minutes from airport.

Amazingly thorough Museum about the life of and on railroads.additionally, they had amazing slices of Americana and rooms set up as they would be during a particular era. You can spend a good two hours here if you visit all the floors and read all of the information. One of the most interesting things to me was an old Sears & Roebuck catalog selling everything including live baby chicks shipped to your address! It was on display inside a home recreation and you are allowed to turn the pages to look through it. I imagine people under 30 may have never seen one of these come to their home as I did as a child in rural America.

Beautiful museum with great events for adults. I attended the Flappers and Fizz event for the first time this year and it was so much fun! Great food & music. Huge turnout for the event but it never felt overcrowded.

We went to see the Politics and Rock exhibit. It was great - displays were interesting and informative. Over against the EMP in Seattle, this was well curated. Just enough to enjoy and not feel overwhelmed or frustrated by a dearth of artifacts. My wife is an educator and we both agreed that the rest of the museum was inviting to kids and a great place to take the whole family. It is a treasure.

name: Joslyn Art Museum
reviews: Definitely a go to! Need to get out of the house? This is a go to and they have an area for kids to get creative also! There is so much to see and do. They also have a cafe if you get hungry or need a snack. I took my two year old here and he enjoyed it just as much as I did!

This institution is a blessing to the cultural fabric of the Omaha metro region. Profoundly important works of art available for free viewing by the public is not available in all communities. But here, it is provided and treasured by both locals and visitors. Thank you to the board of directors. We are in your debt.
Loved it! We were under some time restraints so didn't see as much as we wanted. Will be back as soon as possible to spend some more time. Gift shop was also neat and picked up some great items.

Beautiful, well kept museum. Best part is 95% is FREE. The other 5% would probably be for a new exhibition that just opened where you have the option to pay for that or just do the regular free area. It's also very large with many rooms and a cafe there for you to grab a bite so everything is very convenient. Staff at the front desk were very nice

If you’ve ever been to the Freemason temple in Holborn, London it gives the same vibe.  I wish we could have so more time contemplating the images. It was a wonderful way to spend an afternoon. The quantity of paintings are only exceeded by the quality of master paintings. And sculptures.  We had a good time and we talked about the paintings, art, and history.

name: Omaha Children's Museum
reviews:
This place is perfect for kids. It's handicap friendly with tons of things for kids to experience. 
  Second level has a small food court bring your own lunch or buy something there. 
  The workers were so nice and smiles could tell they were all-in to making sure the kids had fun and stayed safe.
   The bathrooms were nice and clean.

This is a great children's museum. It may not look that big on the outside but it is amazing how much there is to do. Our daughter could spend hours here (and we often do). Each space is very thoughtfully designed to be engaging and educational in addition to entertaining. Many activities are as much fun for the adults as they are for the kids. This is one of our go-to activities when our little girl has some energy to burn.

Amazing facility and amazing staff! They go above and beyond for the love of all the kids that visit. Love the different station options, specifically the career area, the ball room, face painting, and most definitely the train upstairs. The multiple ways our kids get to be creative here makes us wanna go all the time.

The Children’s museum is always a great place to take the kids and spend the entire day. The variety of stations keeps us moving and attracts all different types of likes. Our 5 year old son and 3 year old daughter have different interests yet they manage to enjoy the entire time. The upstairs exhibits are always changing so the thrill always remains.

So much to do!!!! Kids loved it!!! The only reason I didn't give it a 5 is because adults are charged the same price as the children ($14) and there isn't much of anything for us. In the dinosaur exhibit area, all of the parents and grandparents were just standing around. Plus the train and carousel are a separate charge. Other than that it's pretty cool.

name: Chalco Hills Recreation Area
reviews: I go here all the time. The trails around the lake are awesome. I think something like seven miles worth of trails.  Great for biking and running.  The best part about this place is their dog park.  It's my dogs favorite place in the world.

Chalco is perfect all year round! We spent a lot of time in the summer and fall kayaking. It has a boat ramp with easy access to get the kayaks in the water.

There is also an 8 mile loop around the whole lake. Tons of greenery, shade, picnic areas, grills, playgrounds, paved trails, non paved trails, and restrooms!

Soccer fields are great, in good condition, great place to go kick a ball around. Also a great place to go biking and hiking there is lots of beautiful trails. This is also a great place for photography if your a photographer or just wanna have some family pictures. I would recommend going here.
I love coming here. I take my pup all the time and everyone here is so nice!

We love Chalco! We bought our dream home that backs up to the Chalco trail and we love it! I have a bee hive back there that makes the best honey you will ever taste.... the park is amazing and we have a lot of fun back there!!

name: Joslyn Castle
reviews: Wow! What gorgeous history right here in our city. As a military child I had the privilege of living in England, visiting their historical places. I was so blessed I always wish to take my kids one day. Don't overlook this gem my 11 and 12 years old boys loved the tour!!

The castle looks lovely. Our guide gave a thorough history of the rooms and grounds. Seeing the restorative process gave me a sense of grandeur. 

Children and adults alike can enjoy this wonderful Omaha landmark.

This is seriously one of the best places you could ever take a tour of. One of Omaha's gems, the Joslyn Castle is a thing of history and beauty, taking a tour here takes you into the amazing lives of the Joslyns and what great people they were and the huge part in they played in Omaha history. Whether you're attending a party or just taking a tour, you will NOT BE DISAPPOINTED! Please. Everyone must go here!

Five stars for architecture.
Three stars for lack of your time.
Four stars is the average 🙂
Outside path was alright, and the construction looks very cool. I wish they would have more access to the inside rather than just a couple times a week on a tour.

name: Heartland of America Park
reviews: Such a very beautiful place. An absolutely beautiful place to visit. The tropical garden area is my favorite by far. There are lots of good food options available as well!!
Such a beautiful relaxing place to go. The kids love going here and then taking a jaunt to the pedestrian bridge. It's generally very clean and very well taken care of.

The wife liked how scenic this park is. To me it was just a very long walk just to see the river. And it could use more benches for enjoying the view. Wasn't a free seat when we were there. Popular jogging venue. Ample parking.

The fountain is absolutely beautiful. The pathways are a really great way to spend time with your loved ones and nature while exercising. It's a great use of tax dollars at work for once. We took a ride on the boat $4 per adult it was great. The Gondola is $25 per couple that's a romantic way to spend time with a loved one(or propose)to the one you love. In the moonlight at the lighted fountain as it puts on it's light show.
Such a pretty place to take pictures, walk around, and take a boat ride. The ConAgra fountain is also amazing!!

name: Fontenelle Forest
address: 1111 Bellevue Blvd N, Bellevue, NE 68005, USA
reviews: I am a big hiker and love the outdoors so spending time at Fontelle forest just makes my heart happy.   The people that work here are so friendly and helpful.   Walking on the boardwalk is a great way to get exercise and being surrounded by trees and my love of animals is always a great day for me.  When the weather is good and the trails are not too muddy I am always in the forest hiking.   There is nothing better than being with nature and the only sounds you hear are the birds and the leaves blowing with the wind.  I  would definitely recommend this place to everyone.

Fun and great exercise for the whole family. We've had a membership since our son was a baby. We'd use the stroller on the boardwalk while our son took his nap. Fast forward to 4 years later, it's perfect exercise for the whole family and tires him down  before his naptime. If we want, we can go off of the boardwalk and explore the trails. When we remember, we bring our binoculars to check out the wildlife. A hidden gem in Bellevue.

Surprising hidden gem in Omaha. really great system of trails, also has a very nice boardwalk that can be walked by all ages, wheelchair accessible. The raptor refuge is also very cool and educational. Would definitely recommend. 
Had an amazing-looking ropes course, did not get to go on at myself but it looks like a lot of fun.

I love coming here to walk through the trails. A good variety of trails, but I would not encourage taking most trails with smaller children. Stay on the main path if you have small children. The staff is always super helpful in explaining the rescue birds and animals that have recently been brought in for recovery. A great place to teach children about how we should respect predatory birds because of the major role they play in the ecosystems of Nebraska.

The best place. The boardwalk is kept clear in the winter, every other season is pure magic 💗 Go by yourself, with a friend, or with the whole family! Extremely low rates for yearly memberships! Had a membership for over 15years with no regrets 👍

name: Homestead National Monument of America
reviews: Very nice historic site. Smithsonian quality layout. Very knowledgeable staff.
The FREE Square Dance Lesson was awesome, the rangers were knowledgeable about the monument and the areas around.

This is the plot of the first homestead. It has an inside museum, and attractions outside such as a cabin and farm equipment. There is an education center, and an old school building that is part of this center as well. There are many trails going through the prairie that are very well kept and pretty to walk along. This makes for a perfect stop during the day, but I would recommend bringing some water with you when you are on the trails, as the closest building can be as far as 1.5 miles away. Also bring sunscreen, as there isn't much shade on the prairie.

Worth the stop!! Beautiful, clean, educational. This place is for all ages. You can spend as little or as much time as you want here and it's free.  The inside has several displays and a well done video. The young man working did a great job explaining the history of the site and the unique architecture of the building. You can walk a few yards from the building and see an actual settler home. Worth the stop!

Visited for the solar eclipse as the monument site was perfect viewing. Bill Nye was there, can’t beat that. The site itself has a nice vantage for the surrounding landscape and the exhibits are very informative about homesteading and what the first settlers had to deal with to survive. Sobering.

name: Omaha's Henry Doorly Zoo and Aquarium
reviews: This has got to be one of the best zoos I’ve ever seen. We definitely walked 5 miles that day and we still didn’t get to see everything. It was an amazing zoo. It was during the winter time and the animals were in a different habitat that kept them warm but we still had such an amazing time and can’t wait to go back in the summer to see them in their normal habitats. Be prepared to pay anywhere from $10-$20 per person for food. But the admission is well worth it!!

Amazing zoo that is affordable, fun, family friendly, and easy to walk. The annual pass is a steal if you have younger kids. Lots of events for both families and for adult's only.

The zoo is world class and it shows. Having visited several other zoo's across the US I can say that it is definitely one of the largest I have visited. The domes are amazing and really help to set the zoo apart from others. 

The train and tram are great ways to relax and see some of the zoo. I only wish you could add unlimited rides to the pass.

Amazing place! Truly deserving of being one of the best zoos in the world. They are adopting better display practices by keeping large cats in much larger exhibits and have done well in their newer Asian Highlands exhibit. The aquarium is stunning and a more recent trip to another country's top aquarium helped to cement how amazing of a place we have in humble Nebraska. The zoo is always exciting, no matter how many times I've been. I will admit though, there is a lot of walking and in a Nebraska heat, you want to be sure to be hydrated, avoid clothing that will chafe, and have good walking shoes.

We arrived at 12pm. 
We started at the desert dome. That alone was sooooooo gigantic. And it took us close to an hour. 
We ended up leaving at 6. Everything was closed already.. we didn't even get to see everything.
The zoo itself was absolutely AMAZING and I can't wait to go back when it warms up!!!

This is the best zoo I have ever seen.  We couldn't see it all in one day as it is so big.  Everything is so well taken care of and it is clean.  The animals have great spaces to roam around in. Highly recommend this stop to anyone visiting Omaha.

name: Bob Kerrey Pedestrian Bridge.
reviews: Unique for me to cross between two states on a bridge over a river. It's not your typical bridge, it's not straight it is serpentine and very well lit with alternating colors. It is a must see if your ever in Omaha, Nebraska.  This city has so much public art to see. I love this town and its community of flavors and and events that keep me coming back.  Two thumbs up. See you soon.

If your passing through it's a cool place to stop.  The idea is a good one even if the amount of "wet lands" they are attempting to "preserve" is no where near the amount necessary for having a positive impact on the natural wildlife. It's great to get people to take notice and hopefully care. Only sad part is the name plates in front of the plants at the NE side are wrong. Kinda would have thought someone should know the differences between types of oak trees and tag them for the public correctly.

What a great bridge to walk with the family. The kids think its so cool when your in two different states. Nebraska/  Iowa #theBob. The Lewis and Clark Ranger station was great! The staff was friendly and knowledgeable.
This bridge is awesome. It's so fun to walk on and I love Bob's social media presence. And now that he has a troll, what could be better?!

Such a beautiful place to go anytime, I always enjoy coming here to clear my head. At night the lights change colors and you can see some beautiful places all over the city. They have a new troll that is by the bottom of the bridge make sure to take a picture with it and check him out! Great place to come as a traveler and be able to stand in two states at one time.

name: Lewis & Clark Landing
reviews: Typically beautiful spot to enjoy the river that is currently going through a recovery period due to flooding.  If you go now you can see upclose the aftermath and power of the Missouri.  Some great monuments to our service men and women and first responders down there as well to explore on a brisk hike!

Love it here!! Bridge is beautiful & a great workout. Love how it is lit up @ night absolutely gorgeous ❣️❣️ The access to Heritage park is nice & really cool with the different bridges. Whole complex set up is quite convenient, you can park anywhere to get out of car & exercise or just chill listen to music, enjoy the beautiful & natural surroundings😊 Whole area is beautifully landscaped & extremely clean/well kept✨💞💯
If you love being near the water, and won't some quiet time,  this is a great place to go, and a good spot is close to the pedestrian bridge.
