It's a really lovely spot for a walk or just to sit on a bench enjoying the view of the river!
Lewis and Clark Landing is a great place to go and relax. The serenity of the riverfront view and the beauty of the bridge and statues and artwork are quite alluring.

name: Pioneer Courage Park
reviews: Best reenacting of our pioneers ancestors strugls through the mid west.
Interesting but a bit small. Not somewhere you would go out of your way to visit.

This is a half block sized park, so not very big. The statues are very detailed, depicting the pioneers crossing the plains. The wagon train is 5 or 6 wagons, pioneers , a hunter with a deer on his pack animal. Very nice spot for pictures, and a realistic historical display.

A small but beautiful little park just on the north side of downtown Omaha. The life-like bronze sculptures capture an important moment in Omaha's time. Being just along the outskirts of the busiest part of town, it's a nice, quiet place to walk to in the middle of a work day.
Very nice tribute to pioneer history and the statues were incredibly detailed. We really enjoyed this spot to visit on our way out of Nebraska!

name: Kenefick Park
reviews: To see the 2 largest locomotives ever made up close is just amazing.
Nice clean place and good view too, it has a really big set of steps so get ready for that, also has a ramp for wheelchairs!

Rich in history, this monument celebrates the past and the future. 

The showcase pieces include the Union Pacific Big Boy 4023 (4-8-8-4 consist)and the Union Pacific Centennial DD40AX 6900.

We didn't get at chance to check out the visitors center but we made our way to the top to drink in the majesty. There is a stopping point about halfway up that celebrates the Transcontinental Railroad meet in Promontory, UT by the Union Pacific and Central Pacific that later became the SP (Southern Pacific)'.

The placards/signs among the way share many forgotten details about both Omaha and Railroad history. 

Whether just passing through or wanting to see something new. This is an incredible look at one of the many things that made America great and what will keep her that way.

Railroads are crucial for commerce.

ABC's Always Be Careful / Expect a train on and tracks at any time

I love this park! It’s a great place for taking the kids and taking pictures. Our favorite part is the Union Pacific locomotives. It’s a great scene at the edge because you can take pictures! Hope you have a great time there and stay safe!
The scenery is great and seems like a great place to take your children..

name: Hot Shops Art Center
reviews: Hot shops is the most amazing collaborative imaginative creative spot in Omaha! Great artist amazing facilities just  A wonderland Fun

Great spot to see some unique items and talk to artists as they create.
We stopped in here as part of the Nebraska Passport program and I'm so glad we went in.  They were blowing glass when we walked in which was pretty cool.  We wandered through the building seeing the various types of art work and we spoke to several of the artists as they were working.  Not all of the shops were open which was kind of a drag but overall this is a really cool place to stop if you're in the area.

I love the Hot Shops. Such creativity and inspiration can be found there. The open house events on the last weekend in April and first weekend of December are not to be missed as every Artist has their studios open and art work for sale. But the building is open 10-4 everyday and the anchor studios on the main floor always have something happening.

More than just a gallery or two of finished art, this place is a hive of activity of working artists creating in real time. With more than fifty studios hosting 80 or so artists, you might be able to watch painting, violin making, glass blowing, sculpting, quilt making, pottery throwing, or jewelry making during your visit. And it's free.
three floors of art studios of all stripes. If you feel down go there and walk the halls. You will see something that will make you smile and meet some great odd and interesting people.

name: DISH Restaurant
address: 1100 E O St, Lincoln, NE 68508, USA
reviews: One of the good places I had dinner at in Nebraska. The service was great and the food too. They have a changing menu according to the season and always have fresh supply.

Picked up a family meal last night of red wine glazed short ribs, kale salad, risotto, focaccia bread and a (GF) peanut butter/chocolate chip cookie. The huge chunk of short ribs melted in my mouth because it was exquisitely prepared! Every little detail provided something of great value, such as the thyme oil (antiviral!) and more. Even the moist cookie, ideally flavored, was beyond what this cookie-lover has achieved on her own! The only place I have experienced such a perfectly cooked piece of meat this size was in a 4-star restaurant in Montreal. We are fortunate in Lincoln, to have a gem like the Dish restaurant!

Dish is the best restaurant in Lincoln in my opinion. I appreciate that they have a seasonal menu that changes based on the availability of fresh ingredients--something I'm not aware of any other restaurant in town doing. Well worth a visit and worth every penny. They also have excellent cocktails.

I’m glad I tried it once! I took my boyfriend for a birthday dinner. The atmosphere was nice and the one entree I’d give a 4/5 to, but the other only a 2/5. 

Given the larger price tag associated with DISH, I expect more. I should either be blown away by the food or at least be really full at the end of a $150 meal. However, I wasn’t blown away by the flavors and I was still hungry. It was definitely fun to try out once, but I do not think it’s worth the heftier price tag.
The best meal we have had in a few months...great service too.. plan on the mussels again on Wednesday

name: Piedmont Bistro by Venue
address: 1265 S Cotner Blvd Ste 38, Lincoln, NE 68510, USA
reviews: Always a great experience at Piedmont Bistro.  Some would say that my lunch would be hard to "beet". The  beet fries were amazing and the goddess salad with salmon is always spot on!

This is a definite date night place for your spouse. Great food. Local drafts and wine specials make this a great neighborhood bistro. 

Ordered the Honey Glazed Chicken and Homemade Potato Chips. 

Honey chicken was excellent, served with Asparagus, pickled heirloom radishes and carrots and wild rice. The chicken is super flavorful and the honey glazed mixes well with the pickled veggies. 

Homemade Potato chips are essentially pub chips with sea salt and peppercorn pepper with a hint of vinegar.  Comes with a french onion dip that is also homemade. A great pairing with a White Elm Elm English Stout on tap.

Great and friendly servers, definitely a great atmosphere with patio outdoor seating in warm seasons. 

Dessert tray looked amazing with lots of chocolate options at the time of review in late Dec 2019.

One of my favorite restaurants  in Lincoln. The food is delicious and the service is exceptional. I always ask for NATE , He is an excellent server, very knowledgeable of the menu and very attentive. Went tonight for their anniversary dinner, everything was delicious and Nate was awesome as usual .
I am never disappointed when I eat there. The food is delicious and expertly presented. The wait staff very attentive. Highly recommend you give it a try.
Loved the environment. The food was great and decently priced. Can make this a regular spot!!!

name: Vincenzo's Ristorante
reviews: First time here and was craving seafood. Presentation was excellent as you can judge in the picture had the stuffed shrimp, shrimp was good but over the most bland simple pasta, tasted just like it was taked out of the boiling water. Not at all impressed. Not interested in returning

What a wonderful dining experience! The timing of our apps, soups and entrees was perfection. Not to mention how delicious it all was! LeAnn was our waitress and she was very kind and gave us great service!

Wow!  I had an incredible time tonight.  This was my first time and I came based on the recommendation of a friend.  Vincenzo's totally lived up.  I started with Crab Stuffed Mushrooms, they were incredible.  I also had the Baked Lombardi!  Fantastic flavors!  Can't wait to come back.
Fantastic service. Great attitudes. Wonderful pasta!  A new goto for me.  And prices were very fair/generous portions.  Thank you.

I usually have a phenomenal experience at this place. Came in and ordered take-out. Lady was very nice taking my order and tip. Then when she brought the food out, she essentially dropped it and ran away, not allowing me to ask if everything was there. We get home to discover something I had requested was not in the bag. I call to address this, and the girl on the phone clearly doesn't know what to say/do. She then, while LAUGHING, tells me they'll "improve their procedures". Will NOT be returning any time soon.

name: Engine House Cafe
reviews: My first experience at Engine House Cafe was a great one! I came here with my family for brunch, and although it was quite busy, we were able to get our food in a timely manner. The food was delicious, and the atmosphere was welcoming. We will definitely be coming back.

I love stopping here for breakfast! The staff is so nice and makes you feel like you're family. It's always busy and full of people which makes it feel cozy, and the decorations give it the feel of the old Firehouse.

Come on come on to the engine house cafe. A wonderous idea and a breakfast for those seeking a hearty and rewarding investment. The service, the food, any atmosphere make for a tradition one may start for their family.
Havelock is home to many great businesses in Lincoln Nebraska. Engine House Cafe is just a great example of what a community can make of itself.
No matter which food item you choose on the menu I assure you a delicious meal. The service is just how you would expect stellar and real. Your servers main priorities are your comfort and satisfaction. 
If you're in Lincoln Nebraska and looking for a stellar breakfast or lunch, then go to engine house on Havelock avenue.
with that being said the one downfall of this establishment is the size and capacity. This does not in any way take away from the quality of this establishment. my one recommendation for this business is expansion. I expect my five-star rating with engine house to hold its presence here on Google as well as in my opinion.
This is possibly the best breakfast dish, ever. Bacon Avocado Eggs Benedict. There is a good reason Engine House is one of the best breakfast places in Lincoln.

Great atmosphere, cool history, amazing food. The service was also unbelievably fast. Like ask for something boom it's there in front of you. The greeter lady was having a very bad day apparently because she was in a very short and rude mood, but the waitress was amazing. My new favorite breakfast place!

name: LeadBelly
reviews:
This is my go-to for interesting burgers in town (I'm not a fan of Honest Abe's, and Five Guys is my place for a basic burger). This place has a great atmosphere, great food, and it comes out pretty quickly. (Side note: The queso is excellent)

However, service felt very impersonal, she got everything right, but there were no extra words exchanged beyond just ordering and paying. Their system using tablets to order and pay makes me feel like I'm talking to someone on their phone when ordering and kills the personal experience for me.

Overall great food, but the service was basically just a mobile cashier, not a true server.

This place is FANTASTIC! The Peanut Butter Stout was incredible! Being from Texas, this place is definitely on my places to eat again! Service was awesome and our food got to our table in about 10 minutes!! I will definitely be back!

Chad was our server and was so nice and informative as it was our first time there. My sister in-law, niece, daughter, and I were in town for the NKOTB Mixtape Tour and heard it was great food from a friend. You guys did not disappoint! I had the Royal Mountie burger and it was killer good! Thank you all for wonderful food and excellent service. We will definitely be back!

Went here on a Sunday night,  friend recommend it. Boy was he right. If you are hungry, I would suggest the Full leaded jacket. It is literally what every midwesterner likes..chili and cinnamon rolls but with a burger and fries..man it is worth try. the wait staff know all the beers on tap so that was good to hear since not all places do that
Service was really good! I ordered the cowabunga burger, it was excellent!! Beer was cold which made my day!! P.S the atmosphere was great!!

name: The Oven
reviews:
Arguably the best restaurant in the city. Hands-down the best Indian restaurant in the city. Food is always incredible and never once have we had a disappointing experience. Service is excellent as well. 

The Cellar is not to be missed in the basement. It's a great option to have dinner (same kitchen as the restaurant), or just to enjoy their wine list (which is the best in the state) and cocktails.
Food was very delicious. Thoughtfully and quickly prepared. Amazing service. Always had our water filled up. Will definitely be coming again.

I have eaten here maybe 3 times in 10 years but the low number of visits has nothing to do with the taste and quality of their food. This place is amazing! This last time we stopped in the waitress was very helpful; she explained everything we asked about which was a lot since I'm not very familiar with Indian food. She interacted with my 2 year old daughter and made our dinner a great one. 

For lots of reasons this is a great place for a family dinner

Honest review being an indian.. Not so authentic flavor, Lack of traditional ingredients.. I would say more America touch rather than Indian flavor.. when you take order please listen carefully and try to give more options.. appetiser Tandoori fish comes with 2 piece and box of rice???

Admittedly, I am not usually into Indian food. But my partner has had a fair share of Indian food and with all of the incredible reviews we decided we had to try it. We got the equivalent of a sampler meal and one of their appetizers with some extra naan. We kind of just felt like all of it was really over priced. And my partner felt that it wasn’t even particularly awesome food. But it has a nice atmosphere and the presentation was good. I don’t have enough comparison to give it less than 3 stars, but I also wasn’t impressed enough to give it more.

name: Parthenon
reviews: Amazing food!  Great service!   Server was very knowledgeable about allergens and the food in general.   She had an amazing sense of humor!   Loved loved the desserts!   So big and decadent!   Also as some of my other posts show bathrooms are very important and this one was pretty good.   Smelled nice and didn’t feel like you are trapped in a too small box.

Cant beat the flavors and the dessert selection. If you want a wonderful meal with lots of food, check it out. We even took home a quart of baklava ice cream. The texture was a little more like ice milk, but flavors were good. 
For dinner, the lamb, the dolmathes and the pastitsios were super yummy!

Yummy yummy yummy! This is one of my favorite restaurants!! It is never bad! Food is always delicious!! Service is always so wonderful! It is a very comfortable atmosphere and reasonably priced!! Also best deserts in town!! Yummy!

Food is quite good overall, ordered pikila for an appetizer which comes with pita and three choices of dips.  Portions were off in my opinion as one dip gets a large bowl while the other two were large spoon sized served on the side. Their version of "plenty of pita" and my version are very different in the appetizer.  Certain drinks even have a one free refill limit.  My overall impression is that the food is good, service is good, but just the "nickel and dime" feeling for extra cost on refills, the small portions of pita is a real bummer.

Always love the Parthenon. You cannot beat the quality & service of this restaurant. The vibe is upbeat & someone is always ordering the flaming cheese appetizer, Opa! This past visit we called for a take out. We selected the delicious Gyro Family Meal. The order comes with gyro meat, pita bread, sandwich fixings (lettuce, tomatoes, onion & clitharacki sauce), plus choice of 2 sides. I always ask about Chef's veggie choice, and was not disappointed this time with Greek style green beans (beans sauteed in garlic with onions & tomato sauce). Highly recommend this restaurant.

name: HopCat - Lincoln
reviews:
What can i say ! I am speechless . . . 
Unbelievable experience , the place is cozy and i  loved the decoration which is fabulous. The staff are so nice when they welcomed us gently About the food, I nearly tried most of the menu just to get taste of the food and be able to give such a review.
HopCat deserves another visit!

Well second time at hopcat.. wasn't impressed. I shared a burger, also got the dipping sauce that was an extra $1.25, that expensive for sauce, normally it $0.50 
soany where,  basically she introduced/ Cheese, or ranch because it really good, was never explain that there was a cost. I also asked why there was a charge for the cheese.. and completely avoided. So company paid for her tip.... Took a long time to check on us. And when finally ready to pay after the questioning of cheese she walked off, had to wait even longer., I clearly had my wallet out, she took off.  Also she try to ask if we wanted more drinks, before we got checked out. Why give me my receipt ,after all that. Shoot if there was a negative chart, this be top pick.

Great beer selection,  modern friendly atmosphere. Priced fairly for the area and quality. I wish they had a little more variety in the menu though. Burgers, sandwiches, appetizers. Some unique takes, but still kind of limited. Either way,  it's a fun place to grab s drink and a bite from time to time.

As is frequent, it was a busy night in the area, and our crew visiting from KC was looking for a place for adults and our young teen athletes. Nailed it! We ate well, fueling up for the next day, and the adults enjoyed the respectable beer selection. Also, Faith was amazing.

Been here three times now and it never disappoints.  Great local beer selection, and the food is on point.  The fries are amazing and make sure to get a side of cheese sauce.  Our server Donny was amazing to our whole table.  Great personality and enough edge he kept us on our toes the whole meal.

name: 9 South CharGrill
reviews: Never been. Amazing food. Servers were great. They might have been a bit under staffed and/or a bit slammed when we got there. We had reservations, we had a table, but the rest of the restaurant was packed. Worth the wait. I had mac and cheese with steak, awesome. Will definitely be back.

I came here on a Wednesday night around 7:45. The dining room was busy but full of vibrant energy. Even though they were busy I was greeted promptly as I entered the door and was readily able to grab a menu. I ordered the Jack's BBQ bacon burger to go and was offered a drink free of charge while I waited. (I'm assuming it was free of charge as I'd already paid for my entree but I only got water so perhaps I would have been charged if I'd gotten a soda). The burger I ordered medium rare was indeed cook to perfection and tasted delicious! The staff was super friendly and offered me sauces on the side right before they bagged up my meal and handed it to me. An excellent Lincoln locale I would recommend to anyone of my friends!

An excellent restaurant off the beaten path. Excellent food, great service, good prices. Their menu is extensive, so whatever you're craving, they will most likely have it. During this quarantine time, my family ordered takeout to go for 9 people. When we went to pick up, there were 2 people; the owner was cooking and a young lady was taking orders. They were amazing and put such care into making sure we had what we needed. Support  local businesses like 9 South CharGrill!
The appetizers were very good.  We had the crab cakes and onion rings.  The fisherman platter and 18 oz ribeye were amazing.  Service was a bit slow but it was worth the wait!

We love the fries nachos here (forgot what it's actually called) . Great portions and tastes good.   When we have eaten in, we got burgers and the we're good. It was cooked to spec (we normally get medium). If getting to go, the bottom bunk may get soggy.

name: Stauffer’s Cafe & Pie Shoppe
reviews: Best breakfast in town. Bring your appetite! Local owners and fantastic service. Get breakfast and a pure to go.

I went to Stauffer's cafe and Pie Shoppe for lunch/but ended up eating breakfast instead.  I found the breakfast to be delicious. My compatriot has the meatloaf and said that it was amazing, much better then she thought it would be.  My goal was to try the french silk pie as I am a big fan of that pie, but I was too full.  The only thing that brings the review from a 5 to a 4 is that the restaurant was too full, and that it took longer then what I determine to be an average time to get our order placed, but once it was placed the food came quickly

Stauffers is that down home cooking you crave.  This is easily my favorite breakfast spot in town I like the number 3 with eggs scrambled, BACON, substitute french friea to replace hash brown and white toast! I don't do much sweeta myself but pies and rolls here are absolutely fantastic. True Lincoln treasure be sure to give it a try!

If you want comfort food and an amazing slice if pie, this is the place to go. In the city, with a home town atmosphere, makes you feel like your back at grandma's kitchen table.  Enjoy a good meal and let your mind wonder to your favorite memory.
Food is always very good here.  Cold winter morning.  I think food sat way to long before it was brought as it was cold, the rest of us breakfast was also cold.  just ruins going out for breakfast.

name: Toast
reviews:
I was very pleased with this place. The staff was good and very informational. We got a table for 4 immediately. They had a decent selection of beers of draft. I had the Santa Fe Burger which was delicious. It would have been near perfect if it had a bigger patty, it was cooked a little dry, but the flavor and spices were on point. The fries were much better than they looked. 
My girlfriend had the steak Mac n Cheese which she loved. We will be going back for sure.

Good quality ingredients, but many dishes are very spiced, so much so that you can't appreciate what you're eating, the salmon cakes, for example. The greens are well dressed though and the cranberry - orange bread pudding has a great texture and balance of sweet and tart. A bit pricey, usually average $25 a person without alcohol.
Had my first martini... Delicious... Server pleasant... Pretty fancy for my taste but definitely worth going back.... Felt like I was on vacation in some trendy city!!!

Great place for a casual lunch,  dinner,  or brunch. Has outdoor seating and a full bar. Menu has great American cuisine in big portions and excellent desserts. Try the fried green beans as a appetizer, you won't be disappointed.

This place was awesome! I haven't been this excited about a restaurant in a long time. It might take a little bit to find it, it's located in Fallbrook, but it's worth the trip. The place was busy then we got there not full but packed. No waiting for seats and service was quick. We ordered the Pot roast Poutine as an appetizer and it came out very fast. My wife got the Fallbrook Special and I got the Smoked Salmon Club. Both sandwiches we're good but the Smoked Salmon Club was the best. The salmon just melted in my mouth. We had the bread pudding for dessert and it was great as well. The price for everything is very reasonable too.

name: Mellow Mushroom
reviews: Unusually busy evening, had to wait for our food.  Food was amazing.  Our waitress was diligent.  The manager made our evening memorable.  Especially for a birthday dinner that started rough, she got the birthday boy to smile more than once!!  We will be back!

So good! Amazing food! Great service!! I'll definitely be going there again. Even better, someone told us to get as much alcohol as we can in before the concert since its even more expensive there. It was awesome!!

Really fun funky laid back atmosphere and easy going staff made for a good relaxed night for excellent pizza, salad  & beer on a stormy evening.  Everything was extremely fresh and well presented.  Beer was nice and cold. And finally a place that isn't afraid to give you napkins, especially when you're eating finger foods.  Diverse menu with something for everyone.  Prices reflect the quality and freshness of our food and worth the price.

Mellomushroom is a gluten free friendly and vegan friendly option. They have vegan cheese as well. The service was excellent. Parking is tough if you go on a busy night and you might need to use a garage. I do not know if they validate parking. My only complaint is that the last few times I have been to this location I have noticed that the bathroom sinks are not working properly.

We LOVE this place. We live in Omaha and will drive out just to eat here. Best calzones you'll ever try! Naomi was a fantastic server and was very attentive! Despite the restaurant being busy, she got us a great table and took great care of us. Thank you Naomi!

name: The Green Gateau
reviews: There are a number of good restaurants in Lincoln, but very few that are as awesome as The Green Gateau.  We have dined here for breakfast and lunch but not dinner. There were 6 of us dining on Valentines Day evening and were seated at a round table in a room towards the back of the restaurant. We ordered everything from an appetizer to desserts with each of us ordering a different entree and each of us claiming our entree was the best. The plate presentation was beautiful and each bite delicious!  From the beginning to the end of our dining experience our server, Alexia, did not miss a beat!  Thank you for a wonderful experience! We look forward to returning soon!

The Green Gateau never disappoints. We are always greeted by a warm, gentle feel every time we walk through the front doors. We love coming here for birthday, anniversary, and Valentine's day meals! The staff is always very nice, and eager to help with wine tastings & selections. My 25th birthday was capped wonderfully with a fantastic meal at the Green Gateau. Like always, thank you for a great evening!
Holy cow... absolutely wonderful breakfast.  I'm not what I liked best,  the lobster Benedict, duck hash or gourmet french toast.
Friendly staff. Awesome food. Cozy atmosphere inside. And prices are great for what you're getting.

Fantastic dining establishment. Had a private event on a Friday evening; service was top notch, food was beyond delicious, and all entrees arrived at the same time. Great appetizer selection, huge variety of flavorful entrees, and desserts put you in a coma. Vegeterian options, great drink selection, and casual atmosphere. Treat your SO to a great 3 course meal, or get together for an event. I will 100% be returning to this establishment. Get the signature Green Gateu Dessert!

name: Rodizio Grill - Lincoln
reviews: Been there twice and had a great experience both times. Their salad bar is great and is a perfect meal, in itself!!! Went when they had the game meats and had some interesting selections!!! My favorite was the rattlesnake sausage. Meats are well seasoned and cooked to perfection!!! Grilled pineapple is out of sight!!! Friendly staff and great service!!! Be sure to give yourself lots of time to dine here!!!

Fantastic food.  We came here on a date night before my girlfriend had a pool tournament and the food was amazing, the staff was friendly and welcoming, and the restaurant was clean.  This was an experience well worth it and I look forward to coming back again.
A great place.  Lots of great food.  The waiters come and cut off the meat at the table. They have a great salad bar.  Very relaxing dining

We went for valentine's day.The food was good and we loved the atmosphere. The only negative experience was the service. I could have attributed this to the busyness of the restaurant with it being such a busy night but most of the tables were empty when we were there. We had to wait and wait until we saw our waitress and then remind her of things that we had asked for more than 15 minutes earlier. My fiance never got the drink he ordered and were in the front area of the restaurant. I may give it another chance but I'll probably just move on and give somewhere else a shot.
This is a high quality restaurant. All of the staff are friendly and there is food for everyone.

name: Buzzard Billy's
address: 247 N 8th St Ste 101, Lincoln, NE 68508, USA
reviews: Fabulous food.  It's been along time it seems since we ate out.  We used the delivery service which was perfect for us.  Everything was perfect.  Thanks for being there.  Wonderful ❣️

Good food.  Pretty good atmosphere. Little on the expensive side for some of the dishes.  A couple of the Cajun combinations were just a tad on the bland side....a little more spice is in order for those of us who know what it should taste like.  Nonetheless, the place was clean, and the service was as it should be.  Would I forget the name of the place....probably. Just  nothing that yanks you back in repeatedly like the Cajun dishes at the Jazz in downtown Omaha.  But, in all, if I was in the area, I'd visit Buzzards again.

So glad I stumbled into this place! Great food and drink menu. Eclectic decor. TVs for the sports fanatics. Got a table before the dinner rush, but when we left it looked like quite a wait. The girls and I tried each others dishes because everything looked as amazing as it sounded. Each dish was chick full of flavor. I can not wait to go back and take my husband.
Great food.  Fast service.  Excellent prices.  Large selection on the menu.  What more could you want?  If you're in Lincoln, I definitely recommend this place!

Experience and food were amazing.  Cat dazzled my friends and I with great service and a sweet scrumptious smile. What a great escape to the bayou.  I felt as if I was in the swamps of the south. I’ll be back to see the southern kitten, what a pleasure to experience the smooth purr of such a fine feline. 
The cats Meow.

name: Single Barrel
reviews: Was just driving though town and stopped by for some dinner. The food was amazing! I got a pulled pork sandwich with eggplant chips. The eggplant chips were so crispy and delicious! I've never had anything like it. My sandwich had really good flavor. My dad got a hamburger and loved it too. I wish I lived closer so I could go back!

My family and I loved it. It’s a bit pricey but you get what you pay for. Everything looked so good! We will definitely come again. My son thought he could eat a full rack of ribs, but quickly realized his mistake when the food arrived. 5/5 some quality meat and bourbon.

So glad you are willing to be open for carry-out during this difficult time!  It is truly appreciated since I was staying at a hotel and had to go out to get food. I couldn'ttake another day of pizza or junk food. My steak was absolutely wonderful and perfectly cooked and the potato cakes were great too!  I will be back!!!

Excellent selection of whiskies and the pulled pork is quite good.   The ribs and dirty rice were over-cooked, but their flavor was good.  Maybe a bad batch.  I've been here before and both were tasty and much better that this go-round. I'll be back.

The foods great and their whiskey selection is indeed impressive!  That being said when I entered in my last visit the host who would normally welcome the guest was asking if I was lost and if I needed something.  It came as rude and presumptuous that and being profiled came as a shock.  I was hungry and not one for confrontational and told her we're here to eat, so at least that message got across.  Food 5 starts, service needs work.

name: Cracker Barrel Old Country Store
reviews: When I went January 1st, 2020, unfortunately someone passed out or something and 911 had to be called. All the workers, staff, and waitresses were all calm and chill about it. Our waitress Brooke or Brooklyn I don't remember her exact name was amazing. She was super nice and smiling all the time and I would definitely go again because of her! Amazing service!
It's the perfect place to come for a hearty meal at a reasonable price and enjoy a warm fire on a snowy day. Other days it's still great. Hard to get seats Sunday mornings, though.

The food was amazing and the waitress was the nicest. It was my first time there. So she told me the history about the restaurant and I learned some pretty cool things. The game with the pegs on the table was fun, even though the least of the pegs I could get was 4. I had a good experience.
Are you a fan of country style cooking? Do you enjoy great atmosphere? Do you like your table to come with a brain teaser?? Then of course you already enjoy Cracker Barrel!

Great food, great service for a great price! I had the open faced roast beef with mashed potatoes and gravy. It was delicious! I added a side of fried okra which was yummy too. I recommend this for anyone looking for a great meal!

name: Cheddar's Scratch Kitchen
reviews: A fabulous family dining experience, but watch out this is a popular place and you may have to wait while to get a seat. The sirloin steak and sides were quite delicious. It's obvious all their food is made fresh. Even my gluten free family members found satisfying options for their meals. R didn't wait too long for the food especially considering the place was packed. I highly recommend Cheddar's for a great family dining experience that shouldn't break your budget.

Our family ordered the Lemon Chicken Meal for 4 last night, with the sides of French fries, Cole Slaw, and an extra small side of Broccoli Casserole.  It came with the amazing croissant  rolls.  Curb side pick up, right on time when they said they would have it, and seriously, it was all delicious!  Would have it again!

Wasn't the worst food I've had, but wasn't real good either. My daughters mac and cheese was cold in the middle like it was microwaved, and my chicken strips were very salty. So not to happy with the food considering the price.

Showed up about an hour before close and the restaurant wasn't busy but it was a week night so kudos to the staff for being so quick and courteous to help me!
My order came FAST and it was pretty good!  The bartender was in good 'spirits' and had a smile on her face each time I spoke to her!
Would've given 5 Stars but they did not have Free Wifi and my phone went to 3G as soon as I entered the building (1st world problems, I know)!  In a world filled with technology, maybe it's a little subtle hint from Cheddar's to enjoy family time and stay off your phones!

The food quality is good. The atmosphere is awesome. The fish tank is beautiful to look at. Love the decor. Waitress was pleasant and fun. She definitely forgot to bring me my potato soup. That's okay.

name: Honest Abe's Burgers & Freedom
reviews:
Honestly, It’s Good
On a whim, with nothing to do, I traveled to Lincoln, NE from Omaha for a day trip. When I did a search for the top ten best burger places in the area, Honest Abe’s Burgers & Freedom was at the top of the list. So, with an empty stomach and a big appetite, I went for the challenge.
Located on the corner of a shopping center, the restaurant isn’t fancy when you step inside, but there is a clever history timeline on the wall that you can read as you wait in line. Pay attention because there are some fun additions related to Abe and burgers written in.
The chalk board menu at the front of the restaurant lays out everything you may want before you give your order to the cashier. For me not only is the burger important but so is the bun. My “Greatest Burger Ever” selection was not only juicy with all the toppings that are offered along with their “awesome sauce,” but the soft, pliable bun held it all together. Since the menu is a la cart, for an additional 3.75, you can add the freedom fries, and a drink. It was a pleasure meeting Ben, who’s customer service skills were on point.
Overall: Honestly, it was the best burger I’ve had in a while.

Perfectly cooked burgers EVERY time we've visited!  Truffle fries are spot on!  Even the fountain coke has the perfect carbonation & syrup combo!  The shakes are incredible... I won't order because I'd drink the entire thing but you know I encourage the kids to order one so I can try it!  🤣

As burger places go, this one seemed pretty darn good. The menu is up on the wall and there are several regular burgers and a few specials that change. The decor is quirky and features Abe Lincoln all over.

My burger came quickly and was well cooked. Special attention was paid to the toppings and the bun is high quality, so although it's a large burger physically, it stays together and is structurally sound. The fries were great, but I didn't need many of them after eating the burger.
burger and fried are awesome, awesome s very tasty. meat cooks perfectly. love to see the writing menu on the wall

I'm not from Lincoln but was told this is the first place I needed to come for food. I am so glad that I took that recommendation because this is one of the best burgers I've ever had in my entire life! I had the fireside Burger which consists of many different ingredients one of which being jalapenos but it was not too spicy at all don't let that scare you away. it also has toasted cumin on it which was a great addition to this burger. A must order are the parmesan truffle fries with awesome sauce. I will definitely be back and we'll try many different burgers next time.

name: Heoya
reviews: We enjoyed what we had from Heoya! Yummy and delicious! All food is prepared when you order. The owner is super friendly and courteous! When we asked for more information regarding a couple of dishes, right away, he shared some samples with us. Even though this restaurant is located inside the gas station but we still had good time dining here. There are four tables and plenty of sitting.  The nice thing is you can purchase a drink from the gas station to enjoy with your meal. The restrooms are clean as well. We will visit again for sure! Highly recommend this place!
We frequent this place almost every Friday for work... it’s great and different than anywhere else in town!

This place is WORTH the hype. Hands down. It was absolutely amazing. Our group ordered the Pork, chicken, and Beef rice box and the Korean fries. Everything was so flavorful! The rice box comes with a salad and crab Rangoon. All the flavor just hits ya. And the fries with the spicy mayo was delicious. Such a cool place. The owner even gave us some spicy crab rangoons on the house just so we could try them. They were so friendly and greeted all customers. And the fact that it’s inside the U-Stop just makes it that much cooler. We will definitely be regulars here.

Everything I've tried is delicious, but the Korean fries are at the top of my Favorite Things to Eat in Lincoln List! 
They normally come with cilantro and onions, but I can't eat them, so the staff suggested adding pickled carrots and daikon. I'm so glad they did because it's FABULOUS! I also have to watch how much bbq sauce I have, so they put it on the side for me.  It seems most people take their out of town visitors to Runza, but I bring all of mine here, and every single one has loved it as much as I do!
For those of you who aren't sure, "Heoya" is pronounced, "hell-yeah" Like - Hell yeah that's my favorite place to go!  Those fries make me weep with joy! 😂
This place was absolutely delicious. Quality was amazing for the price and it came out really fast. Don't underestimate this place because it's in a gas station.

name: Sebastian's Table
reviews: What can I say? Sebastian’s Table has always been a place I can reliably go when I want something interesting and beautifully cooked. I was in love from day one on 14th Street, and I’ll still be knocking back sangria, sprouts, and smoked Gouda dip until the day either I or they shut the doors for the last time. (Extra stars for the inventive and unfailingly genuine bartenders!)

Upscale casual atmosphere. Reservations are a good idea, but not required. Serving sizes are smaller, but the dishes are excellent. My wife and I walked out satisfied. Everything was will prepared and flavorful. The staff was very friendly and helpful.

Excellent and well thought out menu choices. Our table shared the beef and blue, the duck confit, and the octopus and chorizo, which is probably the most unique dish I've tried in Lincoln. And the chocolate stone is also a great choice as a rich and decadent dessert you'll need to share. Our waitress was superb, however, on future visits I'm looking forward to the male wait staff developing beyond the drop and dash.

Forgot photos! But enjoyed immensely. Been there several times with different size groups, friends and/or family. Been pleased every time. Front tables are cold due to breezes from door openings and closings. Servers give good advice and recommendations. Biggest problem is over-ordering because so many items sound delicious and typically are. Continue to return and will for the foreseeable future. Just delicious and very good with reservations and special requests, i.e.bringing small children, which we did very successfully. Highly highly recommended by all of our family and friends.

We love this place whether eating indoors or outdoors. The food and service is always exceptional. We are getting through the menu one dish at a time and have not been disappointed with a single thing. Excellent!

name: Hiro 88 Haymarket
reviews: The food was really good and fresh. I enjoyed the lettuce wraps and all the sushi. There were several happy hours food and drink specials and we also ordered off the menu. They have lots of gluten free options. Our server was very nice and helpful!

Went to Hiro 88 in the Haymarket on Sunday and found it to be impressive. Between two of us we ordered enough sushi to get the boat which I was very excited about when it came. The waitress was very nice and checked in regularly. The sushi tasted great and was very fresh (prior to going here we had bad sushi at ginger). The price was also at a competitive price. We will be back.
Sushi wasn’t as described didn’t taste fresh. I couldn’t even eat some of it.
Hiro 88 was phenomenal, like always! We had a great time with a large table, and received fantastic service. The food came to the table quickly, and it tasted phenomenal.
Refined decor, great food presentation.

name: Billy's
reviews:
By far some of the best food in town
 Upscale with a warm, homey feel. Great prices and even better service. Had a wonderful date night. They also have gluten free and vegan menus. Very accommodating and welcoming. 10/10 recommend.

The restaurant is a beautiful old home with lots of character, the food presentation is appealing, but it may have just been an off day but what happened was ridiculous. First incident. Appetizer was mussels in white wine sauce, some were almost ice cold even though the shells were open, which Isent back. Second. Asked for another glass of wine, brought a different type than my first. Third. When my guest and I received our lamb chops almost 2 hours later, both were at best rare to raw and one was supposed to be medium. We got up explained how disappointed and unexceptional the meal was, tipped our server and left without eating.

Atmosphere is great!  Staff was all very nice and talkative.  Drinks and food were great.  I ordered the pork shank, had a few bites and it was cold on the inside, so I asked Alex the server if they could warm it up.  He brought back an entire new meal!  It was great!  The brussel sprouts in a balsamic reduction were terrific.  Must try.
Amazing dining experience! Chef Nader came to our table to ask about our food needs (vegan) and delivered a fantastic meal. The Brussels Sprouts appetizer was phenomenal!
Love the historical environment. Food was 50/50. Pasta and salad quite good. Dessert was good. The vegetables not so much. Watery. Skip the duck. The sauce on the duck was very good though.

name: The Eatery
reviews: Wanted to stop somewhere for relaxing lunch, and this was a good choice.  The menu has so many item, it was almost hard to pick.  They have a wonderful lunch menu.  Smaller servings, but it also includes a trip to the salad bar or soup, so it fills you up.  Our waitress was in the process of training another waitress, and they were wonderful gals.  Enjoyed their humor, the lunch and the relaxing atmosphere.

Great homemade food, fantastic place to eat. They also fo party groups and special menu for specific events.  The prime Rib is to die for. They do sell wine and beer and have their own bakery with outstanding desserts! Highly recommend you try this place,it will become your number one restaurant!
Great place for breakfast lunch and dinner
They have a HUGE menu and everything I've tried is delicious. LOVE their pizzas and french onion soup. This place is great for any occasion!
Good Food, Great Atmosphere, Kind Employees and Very Personable Managers! It can get a bit loud, but that's a Positive! It means they are Busy and people are Coming Back Again and Again!

name: Wilderness Ridge
address: 1800 Wilderness Woods Pl, Lincoln, NE 68512, USA
reviews: Patio and golf course are so beautiful! Food is delicious and perfectly cooked. Staf are very nice.
Lamb was gamy, prime rib was cold and tasteless, sea bass was very good and the desserts were fantastic.

This is one of my favorite golf experiences in this state.  This state is loaded with great public golf facilities, but this is a cut above the rest.  Great golf holes.  I am never disappointed when the round is over though, because I can't wait to head upstairs and eat at one of my favorite restaurants in town.  Also some of the best golf instructors around.  Course is usually in great condition!  They sunk a lot of money into this place when it opened and it has paid off.  Gotta check it out!

Very nice atmosphere, I loved the wood architecture and design. I got the Hickory cheese burger and sweet potato fries, and liked it. Bud light draw was 4.50 so that was ok. Wasn't too expensive but the service wasn't the best, kinda slow when not a lot of people there. Outside sitting was nice, you can see the golf course. Overall I'd recommend it.
Wilderness Ridge is a top spot in Nebraska for golf, drinks and dining. The magnificent log clubhouse is a Lincoln treasure. You'll feel like you're walking into a Rocky Mountain lodge.

name: Asian Fusion
reviews: One of the best sushi places in town. Staff is always attentive. Quality of food is outstanding. Prices are very reasonable.
Went there for a late lunch and lunch special is great! Was very satisfied with the sushi and cashew chicken. The server was extremely attentive and helpful. Will definitely be going back.
Food is fantastic. Staff is very knowledgeable and friendly. You can't beat Tuesday's an Sunday's all you can eat sushi appetisers soup ECT. For one price

We arrived at about 5:30 pm on a Saturday.  It was rather empty in there customer wise Good time to arrive.  The booths were large and spacious I love the decor high ceilings and open.  Originally was just going to buy a couple rolls then we noticed they had their unlimited menu for $23 a person.  And only $12.99 for kids 10 and under.  The price includes drink. And a large selection of soups, rolls and entrees.  It was my son's first time trying sushi so we got one roll of various types.  We also got hot sour soup.  The hot sour soup was very spicy.  The roles were good, and they were big unfortunately rice made up a large portion of them.  My favorites at sushi restaurants are normally the spicy salmon and or spicy tuna rolls.  But the way they prepare them the fish tastes like it has bits of fried breading inside. This is a far cry from the way I feel spicy salmon should be prepared. Our waitress was very personable keeping our drinks filled and checking in with us to make sure the food was good.  They had light jazz music playing throughout the building it was light enough you could hear it but not loud enough to be a distraction from your meal and company.  The restrooms were clean.  I likely will come back again.  Total price after 20% tip two adults and one child was $76.  It would have been a five-star review but the way they prepare the spicy salmon cost them a star.

Beautiful restaurant, they've decorated beautifully and the flow in the dining room is great, doesn't feel clustered. The dinner portions are huge, so think about sharing, unless you want leftovers. Sushi was fresh and fairly priced, great happy deals as well!

name: Florio's Italian Restaurant & Grille
reviews: You should definitely try Wednesday wine testing dinner here every first Wednesday of each month. For $10 we try 5 different wine plus an appetizer come with it. Our entree always comes with warm bread, tasty soup, good portion of dinner. So many options to choose. Food is pretty good. Seafood section is very yummy and creative.
Excellent food, atmosphere, and table service. We didn't have a single complaint!! I loved the bread and house salad.

Have always had a delightful experience at Florio's. This is my wife and I's go to for "Pasta Night". 

During a pretty bad snowstorm a few years back, they were going to close early since it was so incredibly slow, but then me and the wife showed up. Turns out, we were the first customers to show up since they opened 6 hours prior! I wouldn't have been the least bit surprised if they would've turned us away with how bad the weather was, but they didn't. 

Instead, they sat us down and treated us like true royalty! It was incredible!

To this day, it was truly one of the greatest dining experiences I've ever had!

Food is exceptional. I had the potato soup and lobster/shrimp ravioli with creamy marinara. I drove an hour for it, and yes, it is worth it. The white table cloth is appreciated and worthy of this traditional Italian eatery. 
Here is the thing. The service was not satisfactory. Long wait times for drinks, bussing, special requests, etc. The table next to us got up and left without being greeted. My party as well waited at least a good 10 minutes before we were greeted. 
Again, food was wonderful. Wine is good. We were all satisfied with our meals, but the service was not fulfilling. Although I must say our server is very sweet, I am not a believer that niciety is a virtue.
Love this place. Especially wine tasting Wednesday's!

name: The Oven
address: 101 Pioneer Woods Dr #110, Lincoln, NE 68506, USA
reviews: Let me start by saying I’m usually very lenient on restaurants but I couldn’t let this one slide. It was a very slow evening for them and we (girlfriend and I) were seated immediately. This was unfortunately the only truly fast thing about the evening. It took 20 minutes to get our waitress to our table and the only reason we even got her then was because I had to catch someone else. We were there for almost two hours and we saw her three times total. It took an addition 40 minutes for the food to come out. The chicken and rice were over cooked, and her paneer was tasteless. It was clear we were not a priority. If you’re looking for a good date night spend your money elsewhere. We will be.

Delicious food, friendly and helpful service, great restaurant vibe. When I asked our waitress for help choosing a dish, she proved extremely knowledgeable about dishes on the menu and seemed happy to explain what to expect from each option I inquired about. She was both kind and patient with us and contributed to our enjoyable experience at The Oven. The food was delicious and the portions large: well worth the price (~$15/dish). When we had leftovers, our waitress packed up our dishes into containers and carefully labeled each of the lids with the dish name and date before placing our food back in front of each of us. Good good and service- worth a visit. You’ll want to come back again and again to try everything.

Food was good, dont go here if you want to have a conversation with someone. They seat you so close to others your practically listening to their conversations. If your on a date they have all the tables for two stacked  in a corner. If your eating with a group and they are rowdy, then this place works.

When this place is on point, it's the best Indian food I've ever had. But there's some nights where either it's different cooks, or something else, but it can be hit or miss on the quality. Mulligatawny soup is awesome almost every time though.

This was my first time here. I ordered the Bhutanese Specialty which I thought was delicious.  Came out hot and fresh.  Pricing was reasonable.  Service was fine.  I would recommend trying if you are looking for something different.  There are two locations in town. They do serve alcohol.  Wine and champagne mainly.

name: The Hub Cafe
reviews: Some of the best food our family has had in a long time. We all tried something different and it was all very good.

This is a great place e to grab a bite to eat or a cup of coffee and even a beer.  The view is great and they have outdoor seating.  The food was very fresh and hot, service was great but there can be a line here during peak hours but definately worth the small wait time.  The avocado toast and skillet were great I added a egg to the skillet made it even better.  Will be back for sure.

Fresh locally sourced ingredients.  Vegetarian, gluten free, coffee/tea, bar (beer, wine, & cocktails), and to-go items avaiable.  A cozy modern cafe with beautiful views, located right on the bike path.  This place has quickly become our favorite weekend go to.  Service is very helpful and friendly.  An excellent healthy option cafe.
Perfect place for brunch. Mimosas are really good. It gets very crowded on weekends, so plan accordingly.  Service is really nice and food is exquisite. I will definitely come back.

This is a really cute little cafe! The food is fairly upscale for Lincoln, but fairly priced and well worth it. It has indoor seating and a few patio seats overlooking the creek in the back. Definitely check it out for a great brunch!

name: Tiru Ethiopian Restaurant
reviews: From the minute walking into Tiru Ethiopian Restaurant you are greeted with a pleasant ambiance with smiling staff tranquill music and refreshing aromatic scents all beckoning you to sit relax and enjoy your meal, with a vibe complicit to the Ethiopian culture of actually sitting to enjoy your food. There is no rush service it's just simply relaxing. The cuisine is truly enhanced with beautiful flavorings of spices and herbs, it just melts in your mouth, the spiced tea is delightful before and after dinner, to enjoy with your Pierre sparkling water. If a person is looking for a new food experience with culture, fine cuisine, relaxing environment and staff that aims to please Tiru Ethiopian Restaurant is the place to go to.

This place is fabulous! I enjoyed their variety as well as the sense of authenticity this place exudes. The restaurant is clean and the staff pleasant. We walked out full and smiling.

All that said, I would recommend calling ahead to make sure they are indeed open, especially for Sunday lunches.

How can food this delicious be this economical??!? SO GOOD!
4 of us got the vegan plate and the meats plate to share, so good. The enjara is mild and yummy. Also, the hot tea was very nicely spiced. Totally coming back here! 
Does take just a little time to cook, but we didn't mind the wait at all.

Delicious food!  We tried the mixed meat platter and enjoyed it all (two lamb dishes, one chicken, one beef).  The flavours were all different, and the chef/host adjusted the spiciness to our liking as it was made fresh.  Aside from the spice accommodation it seemed authentic.  The restaurant is new so you may not have heard about it.  Hoping this one stays!

Wonderful food!!!!  I highly recommend it.  Someone described Ethiopian food like this "if you like Indian food you will love Ethiopian."  For me it was the perfect way to describe Ethiopian.  Yesterday was my first time ever eating Ethiopian and I am finding myself thinking about it today.  Thank you Tiru for sharing your culture and food......I will be back!!

name: AmuManu Ramen Bar
reviews: Great lunch the Ramen was delicious and I was very happy that they had Gluten Free options. The staff was courteous and helpful when choosing my meal. Service was fast and the food was filling. Will be coming back again.

I was a bit hesitant going here because I'm not very 'cultured' in food. I get the same things every time at the same restaurants, I'm kinda picky and dread trying new things, but this was a great experience! The staff was very knowledgeable and helpful in deciding on what to order (since I had absolutely no idea). My aunt and I shared the 'octopus meatballs', I can't remember the exact name, but they were amazing! After that we each got our huge bowls of ramen, which tasted very good.
Tasty food and quick and friendly service. You’re able to add/subtract any topping from a dish on the menu.
Absolutely delicious. You can taste that the broth and chashu are made in house. The options are extensive and very customizable. Everything was perfectly made.
Just amazing food, easy access, great customer service, low price. I tried it all, My favorite is Tan tan meh (spicy noodle with peanut broth). Appetizer is small size and little bit expensive.

name: Mazatlan Mexican Restaurant
reviews: All I can say is WOW.  What a horrible service.   A day they knew they would be busy.   Call a Togo order in at 6 pm and finally out the door at 930 pm.   Not much different from a regular dinner service...  you would think after waiting over 3 hours the food would be immaculate instead we recieved a pile of food all mashed together....
Great guacamole!! Fantastic service! Excellent portion sizes for the prices!

Chips and tortillas are home made.

House Salsa was good.

We had the jalisco fajitas for two. Wonderful. 

Professional staff with beautiful smiles.

Their Margarita should be categorized by the Roman Catholic Church as a mortal sin.

Delicious giant margaritas! Extensive menu choices and fast, friendly, attentive service. Whether I order the veggie fajitas, guacamole and chips, or anything else - Mazatlan never disappoints - everything is scrumptious. They offer a large outside dining area as well as the large inside seating area. They treat you like family at Mazatlan - what's not to love?
You know what your getting before you every leave your driveway. Yum yum one of the top rated ethnic foods in lincoln

name: Ginger Grill
reviews:
The food is always great. The place is really clean and pleasant. We had a reservation for 7:30pm and ordered food around 7:40pm. The cooked meal came out around 8:00pm. Then 10 minutes later the appetizers came out. However, it took 45 more minutes before the sushi rolls came out that we ordered. I sat there for 35 minutes with my food on the table while my date waited for her sushi rolls. 

We were told by our waiter that there would be some kind of comp for the amount of time we waited. And for my food sitting on the table for so long. We were also told the manager would stop by to check on us but that never happened either. We got the bill with no discount or visit from the manager. 

This used to be a great spot southeast Lincoln for sushi.

I would recommend you head to a different sushi place to be served correctly.
Yum! Lovely atmosphere, my husband's Korean ribs were perfect. Sushi was a little loose, but tasty. Ginger vegetable soup was spicy and good on a cold day.

First off the atmosphere here is just best. Knowledgeable staff very prompt.  Food fresh tasty. Very interesting menu. Will visit again.
Better yet place one in Omaha.

Our first trip was good, second was awful (hostess wouldn't seat us in the bar to have drinks, even though it was completely open and was super rude about it)...so I swore I wouldn't come back. Then tonight I ran into friends from out of town and they told me to meet them here. We sat in the bar and had a great experience! Dylan was amazing. Incredibly friendly (and patient while we kept visiting between ordering), as well as knowledgeable on menu items, and witty. The lettuce wraps with chicken (and Dylan's recommendation of peanut sauce) were delicious. The Yummy roll held up to it's name. I'd also recommend the Original Sin blackberry Black Widow cider. I'm giving this experience five stars and hope this level of service continues when we come back.
The food was great.  The menu is priced reasonably and the service was very good.

name: Issara Modern Asian Cuisine
address: 1701 Pine Lake Rd #7, Lincoln, NE 68512, USA
reviews: After a good experience at their sister restaurant, Blue Orchid, I was definitely expecting more and better. We again had a large party as we did at the BO, with 15+. The food was not as consistent, but some of the flavors were definitely there for most of the dishes. I enjoyed my blue crab fried rice, but it could use just a little bit more crab. I also don't recall the description mentioning tomatoes otherwise I would have excluded it. That's important to me for allergy purposes. The pan fried halibut was also good, but small and a little dry for my taste. I also tried the duck which was very good. They ran out of Thai tea at 7pm on a Saturday night, so only a quarter the table could order it. How does that happen? I'm hoping it's an isolated experience and hopefully won't be a consistent problem. The other party members did enjoy their time and their food, so I think it's still worthy of the 4 stars.

Delicious food. We've come here several times and the food has been excellent every single time. We've always been seated immediately. I'm surprised there hasn't been a wait the 3x we've been. We've been at 6pm, 7pm and 8pm on either Friday or Saturday.
Excellent, we sat on the patio. Weather was great and so was the food and service.

Would’ve given 0 stars if I could. Beyond awful experience. It was Valentine’s Day and we had a reservation. It took over ten minutes to even be acknowledged by a server. And that was after my husband went and found someone. Then we waited over thirty minutes for our appetizers and drinks and we never got them. We had to ask the server to put water in the glasses on our table. There was no bartender or manager helping out. We eventually left and went to another restaurant because it was beyond pathetic. We will never go back. There are other Asian restaurants in town that take care of their guests and properly staff their establishments.
Definitely the best Asian cuisine I've had! The food was delicious and it wasn't too busy on the weekday so it was a very pleasant meal.

name: Texas Roadhouse
reviews: This is our new favorite steak place. It can get a bit messy with the peanuts, but that's kinda part of the atmosphere. The food and service is always good. Be sure to call ahead or you will be waiting. We tend to eat around 5:30. They are usually quite full even that early.

Good steaks, their rolls with the cinnamon butter are great, and a fun atmosphere! Our waitress was very good at her job! However it was absolutely packed. It may have been a Friday, but I feel like they should have a second location or something.
Excellent curbside service!  Quick and efficient.  Staff were appropriately masked and maintained needed social distancing for attending customers and food preparation was great!

Great food very much so comfort food. Very good customer service. My kids love that you can throw your peanut shells on the floor, the have barrels full to snack on. Even when full can still have a pleasant meal and hear each other talk. USUALLY VERY BUSY AND ALWAYS HAS A WAIT. Validates the fact that it is a wonderful restaurant, but everyone already knows.
LOVE there ribs best ever. Leftovers are also always amazing even cold. Love the rolls n butter always warm n perfect

name: Pho Nguyenn Restaurant
reviews: I love this place! The food is always amazing. And the service is awesome. I came here almost 3 times a week while pregnant! Highly recommend!!!

This is my favorite place to eat. I discovered it in college, when my roommates from China wanted to long life noodles to celebrate a birthday. That day, I was introduced to pho.

For the next few years of living in Lincoln, I would eat pho at least once a week, trying new places, but always returning here. The broth tastes richer and contains a more complex flavor than all the others in town. There is a nutmeg aspect that I have never even tasted elsewhere.

The service has always been good. The family who ran it knew I liked spicy and would bring me special sauces they made for themselves from the back.

Now I live in Omaha, some ways away, and I mostly just have to be sad about how much better the pho is there than at any place in town.
First time having Pho. I was pleasantly surprised as to how good the food was. Very kind server, very helpful. We be returning soon!
Best Pho in Lincoln. After visiting several vietnamese restaurants in.the city I've settled on this one being my favorite because of the relaxed atmosphere, friendly staff and amazing food.

Who knew you could get world class Pho in the middle of Nebraska? This was excellent, and I consider myself a tough critic having eaten it all over. Service was super friendly and fast! Highly recommended.

name: Honest Abe's Burgers & Freedom
reviews: Great burgers, lots of amazing toppings and rotating burger of the day. Even the kids loved their food which can sometimes be tough to please.

Honest Abe's true strength is it's variety of unique flavors. If you are looking for high quality patties I would say this isn't your place. But the different burgers and fries, as well as their unique rotating menu was fantastic. Their alcoholic shakes are quiet good as well. However, my partner mentioned that in our meal there were a lot of competing flavors, I would agree but whose fault is that but our own I guess. Fun atmosphere including a private dining room. Fun place to bring friends from out of town.

The awesome sauce was awesome! First timers was excited by unique menu choices choose 1809 and named "Greatest burger ever" staff very friendly and brought to the table. The 1809 was so good!! Balanced cheese and apple burger. Well seasoned fries!! So good!
Reccomend coming here for a great meal!

It is a tad messy with all the sauces use napkins!

We frequently visit this establishment and we absolutely love coming here. We always have to get a double Dutch fudge chocolate shake. We love to sit on the top perch & play checkers while we wait for our food and enjoy our shakes!

The food was good minus the parmesan pile on the lack of fries 🤣. But we'd go back because the burgers were so good! The service however was lacking. The young lady taking orders couldn't be more thrilled to be there (sarcasm). We received our food and asked for a knife as my arm and shoulder are broken. It's easier to cut a burger in half to eat as they are very large and juicy. She said we're out of knives and just walked away. You have 0 knives and 0 enthusiasm for customer service. 😬

name: Carmela's Bistro & Wine Bar
address: 4141 Pioneer Woods Dr, Lincoln, NE 68506, USA
reviews: Every time we come here, the portions, service, and quality are of the highest order! Well worth every penny! I'd recommend it in a heartbeat! It's my wife's favorite place to go! If you have not already been here, GET HERE FAST! Also, they have some of the largest crab cakes you'll find that taste this good!

Terrible experience.  Our wait person was miserable, I hope it was just a bad day and not how she normally treats people.  We ordered bruschetta, which was just garlic bread with a few tomatoes, a salad, steak and the lobster mac and cheese.  I wasn't asked how I'd liked the steak done (came out well done), the lobster mac and cheese was basically noodle soup and you thankfully can't mess up a salad much.  For $100+ I expected better food and service.

Awful service and management. Do not run a business if you can not simply keep up with dealing with guests that come and pay for your food and service. Awful employees trained by horrible owners with no respect towards anybody. Try opening a truck stop to match the service that I received tonight. For anyone looking to see if this place is worth it, it's not. Head to Venue across the shopping center, you will actually be greeted there.
Came here for our anniversary. Dinner was amazing! We both had the rib eye. Atmosphere was very "romantic".  I'm sure we will definitely make the drive from Ashland again.

We had dinner here last night and had a terrible experience!  We ordered the cheese board and it came out with a moldy strawberry and cheese that we hard due to being old.  The side salads were good, but we ordered the Chicken Parmesan for the main course to share and the chicken was not fully cooked. I had lost my appetite by then.  Our waiter was great and it wasn't his fault, but for the prices I definitely expect better quality food!

name: El Toro Mexican Restaurant
reviews: This has been my favorite Mexican restaurant my entire life. Their food is always incredible. I absolute love the fajitas!! They come out still sizzling 😋. The chips are warm and the salsas fresh and delicious. But one thing that makes this restaurant stand out to me is the customer service. The servers are always in a good mood and the order is always accurate. They all work as a team and always give the best experience. You will never hve to ask for a refill on chips or water. Come here for authentic amazing food!!

El Toro has been our favorite restaurant for years.  Tonight we got takeout, and it was wonderful, and abundant servings, just like usual.  We even got margaritas, none can compare.  We called in our order, to get our specifics (like no dairy) on one dinner. Please get takeout!  Keep El Toro going.  Great food and good people.
Huge portions and tasty margaritas.  Take out was done on time.

It was a late lunch for us and we walked by. We have never had before and heard good things! And it was delicious!! We were waited on promptly with a smile. Try he food came out hot and my girls ate everything up!! They wanted to lick the plates! So good! We will be back!

Perfect spot to meet with an old co-worker and catch up! Quiet enough environment to hold a full conversation without interruptions. The food definitely surpassed my expectations for it being my first time there!

name: La Paloma Restaurant
reviews: I go to and review a lot of restaurants, this was an outstanding Mexican restaurant. In discussing what to order the owner recommended shrimp fajitas with guacamole and flour tortilla chips, based on my preferences. Everything was outstanding. Great food, great service, great atmosphere. Highly recommend this place

La Paloma has some great food.  Some authentic and some Tex Mex styles make everything yummy.  The Verde sauce for the enchiladas is just perfect.  Rice is flavorful and Al dente.  The service is always friendly and in point.  Salsa and fried flour tortillas are a nice welcome they deliver to you as you are seated.  This is one of my favorites in Lincoln.

Chips were burnt. Rice is possibly the the worst I have ever had, not fully cooked. The rice flavor was not good. Let's move on the the taco. They tried to fry the taco but it tasted like they put in in the grease for 10 second then flipped and repeated. Very chewy. The beans were ok. The tostada was a tostada. The enchilada sauce was decent at best. The one thing I can say is their friendly people. Thos restaurant probably will not be on my radar again.
Great food (order something new), we love the coconut margarita and if you sit at the bar you’ll have a great conversation with the bartender.

Service was excellent. Warm homemade chips and salsa were very tasty. Entrees we're very good but the side of refried beans were a little bland and the side Spanish rice had hard rice in it. Margaritas were very good too. I will go back but probably get different sides.

name: Gate 25 Bar and Restaurant
reviews: Went before a concert. Place was packed, but staffed for the rush. Food was good.

Great little night spot for dinner and drinks. Drinks are strong like me and the dinner was tasty and expensive, also like me. Nebraska is pretty amazing and the area around Gate 25 is pretty hip. Lots to do and see here. Had a great time.

Great & comfortable set up in this trendy spot. Circular bar leaves plenty of space to walk up and get a drink quickly. Highlights of the menu include the lobster roll and the Cuban sandwich, we had & enjoyed both. Service was solid. Nice gastro-pub addition to the area, with generous pours and a friendly atmosphere, even if you aren't a Cornhusker. Best Moscow mule in the area.
I went to grab some lunch and ordered a burger.  It was just fine.  Nothing to brag about.
Wednesday night deals are the best! $6 burgers (that are delicious), $3 draft beers (good selection) and BINGO

name: Koen Japanese BBQ & Sushi
reviews: We have been going to Koen since it first opened and were not even open every day yet. The staff is phenomenal and food is terrific. Enough food to make it well worth the price. Keep it up and we will continue to eat there and enjoy such a wonderful experience.

Koen Japanese BBQ is truly a unique experience.
The meats are tender & very well marinated for Awesome flavor. They have a large selection of cooked and raw sushi and sushi rolls. 
   Sunday's are happy hour ALL DAY, and you will LOVE the deserts. They have a knowledgeable staff and very clean high end layout for dining and nice bars.  You will be happy you went.
   FYI, the lava cake is a five spice traditional that is out of this world.
New FAVE place for fun indoor grilling and AWESOME appetizers.
Gotta have the Crispy Rice withTuna, avocado and caviar.  Also LOVE their take on jalapeno poppers, sliced, and prep's like nothing you've had before.

Terribly disappointed. Constant inaccuracies - I ordered two sushi rolls and received three. I would recommend when ordering, go though and double check they have written down what you requested because I just paid for the extra roll that I didn’t request, I wasn’t going to complain because how do you dispute an order. Then, we were there for happy hour (which is all day Sunday!!!) and got miso soup which would be $2 for happy hour and were charged $3. Also, got a salad which should be $4 and was charged $5. They fixed it when I questioned them about it but no apologies. Also one of the rolls said it was supposed to have tomatoes on top and it had spicy mayo. So overall, I was over charged, got rolls I didn’t ask for, and incorrectly made rolls. Also the salad I ordered came last? Salad for dessert anyone?

This is a 5-star restaurant. I dine here for world-class sushi and can't believe it is here in Lincoln Nebraska! Koen, Kinja & Shogun have the best cuisine! The rest of the sushi restaurants in Lincoln cannot compare. If you have kids, Shogun is the best choice!  If you want the best Sashimi & Sushi Koen is exceptional!

Hands down the best sushi in Lincoln. I did not expect to find this quality of sushi in Nebraska. The sushi here is on par with high quality sushi in larger cities.  The grill food was also very good. My only complaint was that the gochujang was too sweet.

name: La Paz Mexican Restaurant
address: 321 N Cotner Blvd, Lincoln, NE 68505, USA
reviews: Not the best Mexican in town. Margaritas were okay, but the food was subpar. Service was young and not super attentive. Atmosphere was pretty dated and menus were crusty 😬

Went in for lunch. Service was excellent! Food was good, as it typically is, but the portions were smaller than I remember them being. Lunch time may have been the reason for that so not a huge deal. The complimentary chips and salsa are some of the best in town, but today the chips had virtually no salt on them so they were kind of bland. One thing that definitely never disappoints was the spicy green salsa (you have to ask for it) that alone deserves 10 stars. Overall a good lunch.

I had a thumbtack in my food. 
Honestly I’ve never had an issue before this and our waitress was spectacular. I still had a thumbtack in my mouth (I bit into it) and the situation was not handled with severity . I just hope this will NEVER happen to anyone else

Terrible food...!!! no cheese in cream cheese enchiladas barely any sauce??? Beans cold n slapped on the plate... had i not been with a friend that bought the lunch i would have walked out. 😢😔
Server was snooty and threw our menus on the table because we asked to be seated in a different booth. The first place She seated us... had us right where everyone walks in.
Idk if ownership has changed in the last few years... i know La Paz used to have been a first choice restaurant for me.
I will Not be going back for a meal unless they make this right.... 
       DISSATISFIED CUSTOMER 😠

Sarah Beth our waitress was amazing and never missed a beat!! I had the cream cheese chicken enchiladas and WOW incredible. So tasty and full of flavor. My husband had the chicken enchiladas and loved them as well!! If you are looking for good authentic Mexican food this is the place to go!!!!! Also make sure you try there desserts!!!

name: Copal Progressive Mexican Cuisine
reviews: One of my favorites in Lincoln!  Copal caters very well to people with dietary restrictions.  They have gluten free and vegetarian options.  There are many menu options around $10.  Feels like you are eating higher quality food than typical Mexican food.  Would recommend to anyone!!

Who knew such great food was available in Lincoln? I was skeptical to try a Mexican restaurant self described as progressive for fear of them putting a kooky spin on classic dishes. They kept the experimentation to a minimum and focused on making really delicious meals that made me want more. The hand crafted margaritas were absolutely perfect and the desserts were beyond description.

I've always been a strong supporter of Copal - their food is reasonably priced and their 'premium' Margaritas are quite good!  I'm not sure if something has changed recently or what, but our latest attempt to dine there was a particular disaster.  Understanding that it was national margarita day, and having a party of 7 we chose to arrive early (shortly before 5 pm).  After waiting up front for well over 10 minutes we finally had to walk back and grab someone just so we could put in our name.  We then waited.

Several minutes later a party of 3 walked in and also put in their name.  After waiting for about 10 more minutes, the waitress called the other party and sat them at a table that could have fit 8.  The waitress then told us it would be "about an hour" before we got seated as those people "just sat down".  When asked about why the other party got to go first even though we were there well before them, the waitress' response was "because they had less people".
