I'm not sure on what planet this kind of logic makes sense, but it will definitely influence our choice on where to spend money the next time we're out.

This restaurant was a good experience. It has been there for 5 years before I knew it existed. Atmosphere was good, our server (she went by Z) was friendly and willing to help on choices. Not overly expensive and will definitely be back.
Great food, service, atmosphere!  One of Lincoln's best.  Everything is good and well presented.  Staff are welcoming and helpful!  Drinks are awesome.  Go here, it does not disappoint!

name: Lee's Chicken Restaurant
address: 1940 W Van Dorn St, Lincoln, NE 68522, USA
reviews: It was pretty good, definitely not in its hay day anymore.  I went on a Sunday after church and the restaurant was basically empty.  The chicken was cooked perfectly, potatoes were boxed, and corn was tasty! Onion rings were very crispy, don’t expect them to be cut thick. But service was fast

Food cold, service slow. But server and owner accommodating. I do not mean this as a derogatory rating - Lee’s is an institution here in Lincoln, but the prices and reputation do not reflect the reality. I hope that I gave constructive criticism to the owner in response to our experience. Places like this, locally owned, need actual feedback, not self-alleged victims plying for sympathy whilst absolutely lacking any sense of compassion, or self-awareness, whatsoever. A good place, maybe once a great place; the potential as something unique is there, but the execution is lacking.

Saturday night. About 100 to 130 guests, only three servers. It took over 15 minutes to be greeted. It took over an hour and a half to get my food after being asked by three different staff what I had ordered. The one order still wasn't correct. I understanding staffing is an issue but come on.
One of my favorite places.  The chicken is always good but tried the fish tonight and wasn't disappointed.  Keep family business going and patronize Lee's soon.
The staff was friendy and the food was okay. Lee's has a really old fashion environment.

name: El Chaparro
reviews: I cater with these guys all the time and also eat in. Very yummy and they always have good customer service. Also can I say fast?!! When I cater 40 tacos they have them ready in 20 minutes...crazy fast. The employees work very hard in their kitchen.

Honestly, the only thing I order from this place is 5 steak tacos and occasionally a pineapple water. I get it for lunch almost everyday that they instantly recognize me now. All I have to say is they have the best tacos in town!! I have attached a photo for reference. I accidentally tipped them over so they look a little messy, but they are still good!! As for other food from this place, I have no idea. Never ordered anything else. The tacos are too good to pass up. The staff is also very friendly and make me feel comfortable every time!
One of my favorite places to get food in Lincoln! The service is great!

The service was lovely, and the atmosphere was cozy. I also really appreciate the large amount of food I was able to get with just $6.00- that being said, the steak Tortas I had was amazing! The bread was fluffy, and everything was well distributed on my sandwich. The chips are also perfect. 
I plan on eating here again as soon as I can :)
Nice food with good quantity. Really reasonably priced.

name: Pepe's Bistro
reviews:
Pepe's has the absolute best vegetarian food in Lincoln. The flavors and colors are vibrant and rich. Every dish comes out beautifully plated and perfectly cooked. I love how the menu is small and always changing. Pepe always gives each dish his own unique twist with layers of flavor. 
The restaurant has a friendly and cozy atmosphere with an adorable patio area in warm weather. Pepe does so much for our local community!!!! So thankful. 
My personal favorite things to order are: avacado cheesecake, cucumber lemonade, and guacamole. I can't choose a favorite main dish- they are all AMAZING!!!!!

Pepe is dedicated to providing vegetarian/vegan options to Lincoln using fresh locally grown crops. He loves his community and supports in any way he can. If you’re vegetarian or vegan this is spot a must see and even if you prefer meat, this food is so good that you’ll forget that it’s cruelty free!

Holy buckets this place was an amazing find. Pepe's serves some of the best vegan food I've ever had. It's such a cute and cozy little shop tucked away in the neighborhood of 11th and B. The soups are bomb and I could drink the cucumber lemonade all day everyday. Truly one of Lincoln's little hidden treasures.

This place is amazing. Some of the BEST vegan options in Lincoln. He usually does delicious pop-ups around Lincoln, but he finally opened up his own spot. Even if you aren't vegan, I HIGHLY recommend you go and try Pepe's food. It really is worth your time. Such an awesome place.
Great food and service! It's always a pleasure to eat at Pepe's, and with signatures like cucumber lemonade and avocado cheese cake you'll find yourself coming back

name: Mi Tierra Family Mexican Restaurant
address: 5500 Old Cheney Rd #4, Lincoln, NE 68516, USA
reviews: One of the best kept secrets in Lincoln! I love the food here, the menu isn’t massive but it has a lot of really high quality dishes that always taste great. I love spicy food quite a bit so I was pleased when I ordered the Devils Shrimp here and it pulled no punches! It was a thorough enjoyable experience. I plan on coming back here again in the future.

Great Mexican restaurant! Place has a good environment,  good lighting and decorations, and place looked clean. Upon walking in we were greeted and quickly seated. Then recieved some complimentary bean dip, mild and spicy salsa with chips as we waited for our food. Our order came out in around 20-25min which is reasonable for how busy they were. I was satisfied with the food portions we were given when compared to the price. While eating, our drinks were never empty as they have someone going around every 5 minutes or so filling drinks. Overall would recommend this Mexican restaurant!!

Wonderful, authentic Mexican food! I am a HUGE Spanish Rice and Bean Dip hater, but here, they were both fabulous! I don't know how they do it, but I LOVE their bean dip and the rice is so soft and fluffy. Plates of food were extra generous, I had to get a to go box! Everyone working a the restaurant were very friendly and always smiling! DON'T MISS THIS HIDDEN GEM!
The best Mexican food in town! Great staff! Delicious chips, salsa and bean dip. I've never had a better flour tortilla in my life. If you're looking for an authentic experience, this is the place.

Very clean restaurant. Great Atmosphere! The chips, salsa and beans to start were very good. The main courses were excellent. The staff was very friendly and eager to please! Will definitely be going back again soon!

name: Mazatlan II Mexican Restaurant
reviews: Was very very Impressed. Had amazing fast service with a smile. $7 top shelf margaritas. Was vary authentic except for the season on the meet, which made it even more impressive. BEST Guacamole I've ever tasted in my life and I've tryed alot !

I highly recommend Mazatlan II. The food is great and reasonably priced, but the biggest selling point is their service. Soon after you're seated, someone will bring out water, chips, and sauces (see photo) free of charge. My wife finished off her sauce and literally 10 seconds later a new sauce was brought out without being requested.

Our food was brought out in about 8 minutes after we ordered, in spite of the full restaurant at peak dinning times. My meal was the chicken fajita salad where I requested the sour cream and guacamole on the side. My wife ordered a chicken quesadilla. Both were quite filling and came to about $23 before tip.

The staff are courteous, quick, and accurate, though they are not very talkative. I love this place, we will be back!

Amazing food.. amazing service.. 
perfect for lunch and dinner :) 
I had chicken fajitas and my colleague had Beef Burrito .. he loved the food too 
The service was quick and the food terms were explained on the menu which makes it easy to order.

Sadly, we were not told an accurate account of wait time (45 min became 1.5 hours, though they did bring food wiggly l quickly for the youngest (as requested) the other meals were sporadic and inaccurate.  
They did have fantastic mushroom salsa, and I'm aware that larger groups (7 adults, 5 kids) are more difficult, it could have been handled better.  But I'm going to return, just probably not with a large group.
One of the best quality food I've had in a while. Price was a little high and the drinks were weak I thought but great food ill return. Fried icecream was not good. The cereal coating tasted stale.

name: Imperial Palace
reviews: Fast and polite service.  Great lunch specials and easy on the wallet too.  Cant beat that with a stick.  Highly recommend stopping in for lunch especially.  I love the decor inside too.  So good!

Ordered the general tsos chicken... was the worst I've ever had!!!!!.. was soggy and greasy.... and I didn't even eat more than 2 bites... i paid 23 dollars for the meal.. told them it was horrible and they didn't offer me a refund or anything... I even tipped the delivery guy 10 bucks... so Imperial palace definitely earned this bad review!!!!! I hope no one else gets food this bad...
Great quality food and great value. Fast friendly service and nice retro old school decor. Big portions.

Not good.  We ordered 4 dishes and all of them were terrible.  The “fried” rice seemed like it was steamed rice with soy sauce dumped on it, no veggies or anything. This was the worst Chinese food I’ve ever had.  The chicken was chewy and greasy.
Awesome hot and fresh and the king pau... really had zing

name: Tico's Restaurant
reviews:
Good food, friendly staff, and as a bartender I wouldn't mind being behind the beautiful bar they have set up near the entrance. Building is pretty neat too.

The black beans when finished look like fudge and I thought that was amusing lol

My family and I went there for the first time this weekend. We reserved ahead and when we got there, we only waited about 5 minutes to get our table. Parking is difficult to find if you want to park in their parking lot, since it was full when we got there 6 pm on Saturday night and waited for another car to leave. The restaurant was nice and clean. We had complimentary chips and salsa. Their chip has seasoning and their salsa is very good with enriched cilantro flavor. Menu prices seems pretty average to me. I ordered the chicken fajita burrito and it was good. My toddler does not like Mexican food but did enjoy their chicken tenders and fries. Overall, seems like a good place for gathering! Probably good to reserve ahead and come early to find a good parking spot so you don't have to walk far especially if you have kiddos.

Great lunch and excellent service! Haven't been in for awhile, but will be returning soon. Lunch special was the Deluxe Burrito and it was very good. Food arrived hot, fast, and very nice presentation.

What isn't there to love about Tico's?! Awesome atmosphere, staff, and decor...delicious drinks and food. Incredible variety of perfectly crafted margaritas. Unique and amazing chips. Cream cheese chicken enchiladas are where it's at for the main entree. Ice cream with wine sauce is to die for. Gluten free menu for our daughter is huge. Bonus!

One of my favorite restaurants in Lincoln! The service is always AMAZING and the food is to die for. I am never let down by Tico's! I have to come here at least once a month, otherwise I feel something is missing from my life.

The vegetarian fajita burrito is my favorite item on the menu; it's great!

name: Venue Restaurant & Lounge
address: 4111 Pioneer Woods Dr Ste 100, Lincoln, NE 68506, USA
reviews: Great lighting and warm feel. Customer service was very welcoming with no rush and very attentive. Food was good and flavorful. I particularly liked my mash potatoes. Dessert was surprisingly magnificent which I generally don't have. Will revisit more often...

We told them (in our reservation) we were coming for our anniversary  and they took it to heart! Hostess searched out quiet table in back area on purpose and added a nice Happy Anniversary sheet for table decorations. Waiter offered free champagne for toast, which I'm not aware of anyone else in town providing. Big plus. Ordered 3 from the sea (shrimp, scallops and small salmon fillet) on top of some tasty risotto. Hubby ordered lobster tail and got even better risotto with asparagus and peas. There was enough we each took some home but many people would be able to finish. Will def return and may keep it as a "special" meal location since they made dinner feel so, well, SPECIAL. Also our waiter, Otto, was just the best!! He made great recommendations, was not impatient with my many questions and timed his visits to the table pretty close to perfectly. Know we will return esp when looking for that feeling of being pampered.

Great aesthetics, ambiance, atmosphere!  Our server was very knowledgeable of the menu and drinks.  The food did not take long to get to us, and everything was tasty!  We'll definitely be back for the dinner service one of these soon days (to try the duck breast)!

I ordered the filet mignon today for lunch & it had no flavor. It was cooked too much that it tasted like cardboard. The sides, asparagus & Mac & cheese tasted better then the meat. Do you put any salt or seasonings on your meat?

We were there late at night for drinks, appetizers, and desserts, after a concert. This is one of few classy places open at that time. We had pizza, brussel sprouts, and spinach artichoke dip. All were outstanding. We then shared three different desserts between four people.  Also outstanding, and more than enough to eat. The wait staff was friendly, knowledgeable, and efficient. It's our new favorite place.

name: Sultan's Kite 13th O Street
reviews: The food had no flavor I think cardboard would have more flavor. The green sauce is the hottest they have, I had to ask if that was what I had no heat at all.  The only good thing was someone asked to go with them and they paid. I will never spend any of my money.

Super tasty and authentic gyros and amazing potatoes!  The staff is incredibly friendly and the prices are awesome!  Destination within walking distance from The Bourbon and they are open until 2:30 a.m. on the weekends 😍

I don’t know what they put in their food, but goodness is it addicting. Every time I go the food is top notch, I love everything I’ve had from here. The only complaint I could have is that it’s a tiny bit pricey, but definitely worth every penny with how good it is!

Absolutely outstanding. food! Service was friendly and helpful. Bathrooms were spotless. The lentil soup was to die for, my compliments to the chef's mother and her recipe. Laid back atmosphere, great prices. We will be returning!

It was a nice place to eat, meat was nice, the portion was huge.
Quite enjoy my salad as well. The WiFi connection is OK. nice place to have a lunch here.

name: Grey Whale Sushi & Grill
reviews:
I cannot express how disappointed I am in this place.  Our nephew planned  the proposal to his girlfriend for three months in the Grand Manse, a place with sentimental meaning to them.  His plan was to propose in the foyer and then family and friends would be waiting in the Grey Whale to celebrate with them. 

He made the original reservation three months in advance and spoke with them 48 hours before the big day to confirm our party of 14.  We went to the restaurant a couple hours before the event to drop off flowers and some other special items and were greeted with blank stares. After some conversation we assumed we had the issue worked out and the plan was safe. Forty five minutes before the big event we arrived at the restaurant to find that they had GIVEN OUR TABLE AWAY!!! No effort was made to accommodate us and it was clear they could care less about ruining what was a very special evening. 

Thankfully we were able to make a last minute switch and another restaurant agreed to graciously accommodate us so the evening wasn’t totally ruined. 

To say our family was furious and disappointed would be an understatement.  I would never darken the doorstep of this establishment again if my life depended on it.  Absolutely horrible experience.

My sushi place of choice in town, always love coming here, the food is delicious and it's a cute place for a date.  I'd recommend trying the takoyaki if you're here!  It's delicious, but make sure they cool first.

Ordered delivery, arrived 15 minutes faster than estimated time, came 25 minutes from order time. Best sushi I’ve had in a long time!
The Heart Attack roll and Cornhusker roll are my favorite. I will definitely be ordering more from here

Great food! However, my boyfriend had made a reservation on Valentine's day and it was a mess. We got there early so we were able to get our food but a lot of people who had made reservations were standing outside waiting for the tables to be cleared. People were starting to get really frustrated. The servers did their best to get everything done but they were obviously understaffed. I blame this 100% on management! Everyone else was amazing!
A real sushi place in Lincoln.  Miso and maki were delicious.  They have some very inventive and tasty rolls.

name: Blue Orchid Thai Restaurant
reviews:
Amazing food, upscale and beautiful environment, good service. Seems to be authentic Thai food, and it tastes so good. The dishes have the perfect amount of sauces (not drenched) and are flavor filled. I’ll definitely be coming back. 

The location was a bit difficult to find, so park at a garage or on the street once you’re close and then hunt down the place on foot with your phone map handy.

The basil fried rice was absolutely delicious. I could have eaten it all!! My husband ordered the red curry chicken and I wanted all of his too. It was spicy but we both loved it. Looking for awesome Thai food, find it here.
Great service and as always great food!

Amazing flavors! It was a bit hard to find this place at first, but it's worth tracking down. It is in the center of the block, you have to park and walk to find it. The menu has vegetarian and vegan options. The tofu was perfectly cooked. The Panang curry is among the best I've ever had! If you like Thai food or want to introduce it to someone, definitely stop and check this place out!
Nice quiet place on a Thursday evening. Food was Amazing!

name: Mary Ellen's Food For The Soul
reviews:
Absolutely loved it. From ordering our food to eating it was a great experience. Great customer service and great food. You can’t go wrong with Mary Ellen’s. Thank you for making us a plate! 
P.S. The peach cobbler is to die for. I love it and would love to have some right now!
Always friendly, always delicious. Best spot for food and A+ service.  Definitely worth the wait.

Without question, the best food truck in Lincoln. 

Brisket: 9 out of 10
Pulled pork: 8 out of 10
Potato salad: 9 out of 10
Mac n cheese: 7 out of 10
BBQ beans: 9 out of 10
BBQ sauce (kc style): 10 out of 10
Corn bread: 7 out of 10
Service: 10 out of 10

I'm a certified KCBS judge so know what I'm talking about. Hunt this place down via their Facebook page and drive across town if you have to. Worth the trip.
Amazing food.  The customer service is phenomenal.  Very nice when the owners treat everyone like they are family!
They have great BBQ and you can tell they care about the food and service. They treat you like family.

name: Vung Tau Pho Grill
reviews:
There's a wonderful combo seldom seen, the traditional Pho with thin-sliced grilled pork.  It's amazing.  Everything else is also wonderful!  This food is my panacea. I could be dying of Cancerous EbolAIDS and this big bowl would restore me to full and extend my life-bar. 

Hands down, the best Pho in Lincoln; fight me!

Always good food, especially for the price. A great value. My husband enjoyed his grilled pork. It was a cold night, so I got Pho, perfect thing to warm me up. Nice neighborhood atmosphere, highly recommend. 
If you get the Bahn Mi, ask for broth to dip it in. For lunch, you can get a Bahn Mi sandwich and a Vietnamese coffee to power you through your afternoon for under $10! So perfect!

Awesome . Great food, very reasonably priced, fast, clean, and friendly staff. We got two different Bun bowls, and both were very good. The meat was deliciously seasoned and grilled, the noodles were just a little undercooked so they had the perfect texture, and the bed of lettuce and cucumber was just right. The traditional sauce is served on the side, and there are additional condiments on the table to allow crafting the bowl to your taste. We saw other people having phó, but it was 90 degrees outside, so that was out of the question for us.
Best Vietnamese food in the country. Beef pho broth is incredibly rich and flavorful. Everything is top notch.
By far the best restaurant in Lincoln! Authentic and delicious!!! We have been going there almost every week for a decade.

name: Las Margaritas
reviews: The food is so big and good prices!! So DELICIOUS!! The drinks are big and amazing as welk! Yum yum yum!
Las Margaritas is a great place to go and eat. They have delicious caso (my favorite) and they serve you quickly. I recommend there food and margaritas (the most important part)

Greeted by friendly staff as we entered.
Seated promptly.
Friendly, efficient server.
Complimentary chips with 2 types of salsa (mild & semi hot)
We ordered guacamole and we received a huge portion in a cute pig mocajete, my daughter immediately wanted one. 😊
Food served hot & promptly. 
Delicious & larger than most other places we have eaten at portions for about the same price.
We will definitely return when we visit family again. 💞

We had a perfect experience. It was Valentine’s Day and we came in and got right in up at the bar. We had quick, friendly service. Food tasted great. I think our server’s name was Joel. Wonderful. Will go back!

Attention all other restaurant owners please take note of the excellent service provided at all the Morales Family restaurants. These people have 10 star service all the way. Food is HOTT served on HOTT plate. Unlike a lot of places as of recent all plates come out at once. This seems rare in Lincoln anymore. This place is a true shining example of great business ownership small piece of Vegas caliber service. You won't be disappointed.

name: Dino's
reviews: Walking in the atmosphere feels more like an upscale bar then you're typical family restaurant.  Air conditioning was keeping the place very cool Ladies might want to bring a jacket to stay warm. We had to wait a few minutes for a hostess to come get us and see us.  There was no wait for seating.  We went on a Thursday around 6:00 p.m. The waitress was very cheerful.  It took her a while to get our drinks which was an iced tea and a couple of waters.  I don't blame her it just seemed they were a little understaffed I believe she was the only waitress helping customers at that time.  My tea tasted kind of funky.  Had almost a chemical taste to it.  Though I've had that same taste in tea at other restaurants so maybe at some seasonal flavor.  Either way the tea was a turn off -1 star for weird tea.  I originally came here to get the Reuben sandwich but unfortunately the waitress informed us they were out of sauerkraut.  -1 star for not keeping your kitchen stocked with necessary ingredients.  It wouldn't have been that hard to have someone run to the grocery store and buy some to get you through the day.  Since they didn't have the Reuben available I got the club sandwich instead.  The sandwich was good they used real turkey instead of deli meat which was different but a nice change.  But the bread wasn't toasted very well and ended up being rather soggy.  I feel like the sandwich could have been bigger as well.  I got the parmesan fries on the side they were good but portion size was extremely small.  My son got the bacon cheeseburger it was very good though the meat was just a tad bit dry.  Carrying on a conversation with my wife was a little difficult the acoustics plus the music playing made you have to raise your voice to be heard.  At which point every table around you can probably hear you as well.  So not much privacy for a conversation. After our meal we all used the restrooms.  restrooms where very clean and upscale TVs mounted above the urinals.  The price was about $10 a plate.  Which I feel would be a bargain if my gripes above were addressed.  I doubt we will be back it's a nice place has a lot of potential it just feels like a lot of corners are being cut, and they're severely understaffed for what little crowd was there.

I haven't found a menu item I don't like. I often end up here with a large party and they've been very accommodating each time. Great servers and amazing staff have made sure our experience was stellar.
P.S. Try a boozy shake. You'll be glad you did!

This has to be the top restaurant in relation to the surrounding nearby restaurants.  It is a big place and hosts a lot of people so it's good for big groups.  I know there is a couple different seating sections and I think you could rent one out if you have a big enough party or event.  The food is quality, atleast everything I've tried, and they have some good local beer selections, which I love to see... and drink.

Dino's is a great place for an awesome burger & fries, pub style pizzas, cocktails, and brunch.   Good service, relaxed and clean atomsphere are a standard here.  If you want to watch the game, there are also plenty of screens to watch and enjoy. In an easy to find location with reasonable prices, Dino's is a neighborhood favorite.
Great food and friendly staff! I'd highly suggest the caprese salad with some added medium rare steak. Probably one of my favorite meals anywhere!

name: HF Crave
address: 4800 Holdrege St Suite 100, Lincoln, NE 68504, USA
reviews: If I could give this place 0 stars I would. Not only was the service terrible but the food was overpriced and falsely advertised. We took our daughter here for her birthday. I ordered the risk it for the brisket burger. There was 3 TINY pieces of brisket mixed in with quite literally 3/4 cup of mayo. There was so much mayo it was pouring over the bun. It has ZERO flavor. In my honest opinion I've had better burgers at McDonald's! My husband ordered a blue cheese burger and for some reason there was a bunch of brown sugar grilled into the bottom bun, it had no flavor and didn't even taste of blue cheese at all which is surprising considering how pungent blue cheese is! Our waitress had an attitude and despite the fact that there was hardly anyone in the restaurant she was barely tending to us. Both my husband and my daughter went most of our meal with nothing to drink. For $12 per burger I would expect so much more! Needless to say I will never ever go back.
Absolutely some of the best Burgers, Veggie Burgers, waffle fries and cheese curds in Lincoln. So good for a reasonable price!

Excellent meal.  We just ordered carry out for 6.  They had it ready in minutes for pickup and all 6 orders were perfect!  We had a variety of burgers and we were all quite pleased.  The fries are also amazing.  Thanks and we look forward to dining in when all of this craziness ends!

Ah-mazing!! Came in fairly late, about an hour before closing with a group of 8. They were absolutely happy to serve us, and we didn’t feel rushed at all. This is rare - we go to eat every Friday night around the same time and often feel rushed. Food was great, server was patient and friendly! We even stayed for dessert... the grilled cookie. Huge, we shared among 4 of us. Well worth it!
Great gourmet burger options and the classics as well. Superb taste, delicious! Very fast order and serving. Highly recommend. We will be back to try more of their menu.
